Dot11Type.name: Dot11Type
Dot11Type.description: The current standard supports A, B, G interfaces.

Dot11Speed.name: Dot11Speed
Dot11Speed.description: Specifies the speed in Mbps to use for the interface. A value of 0 indicates auto.

Dot11AChannel.name: Dot11AChannel
Dot11AChannel.description: Specifies the channel number for 802.11A interface.

ExtremeWirelessCountryCode.name: ExtremeWirelessCountryCode
ExtremeWirelessCountryCode.description: Specifies the country code the AP operates in.

ExtremeWirelessAntennaType.name: ExtremeWirelessAntennaType
ExtremeWirelessAntennaType.description: Specifies Antenna type attached to the access-point. The integrated antenna is specified by CTL table on PCI eeprom. The detachable model 15901 is an omni-directional antenna. The detachable model 15902 is a directional antenna.

ExtremeWirelessAntennaLocation.name: ExtremeWirelessAntennaLocation
ExtremeWirelessAntennaLocation.description: Specifies whether the antenna is an indoor or outdoor antenna

ExtremeWirelessPhysInterfaceIndex.name: ExtremeWirelessPhysInterfaceIndex
ExtremeWirelessPhysInterfaceIndex.description: The value of a physical interface number. Each radio on an AP corresponds to a physical interface. There can be multiple virtual interface on each physical interface. The format for the physical interface is xxxxyy where xxxx is the port IF index to which the AP is connected. YY is the interface index within that AP.

ExtremeWirelessVirtInterfaceIndex.name: ExtremeWirelessVirtInterfaceIndex
ExtremeWirelessVirtInterfaceIndex.description: The value of a virtual interface number. Each radio on an AP corresponds to a physical interface. There can be multiple virtual interface on each physical interface. The format for the virtual interface is xxxxyyzz where xxxx is the port IF index to which the AP is connected. YY is the physical interface index within that AP and ZZ is the index of the virtual interface within that physical interface.

ExtremeWirelessChannelAutoSelectStatus.name: ExtremeWirelessChannelAutoSelectStatus
ExtremeWirelessChannelAutoSelectStatus.description: Specifies the status of the channel auto-selection process.

extremeAPTotalAuthFailures.name: extremeAPTotalAuthFailures
extremeAPTotalAuthFailures.description: This variable gives the total number of Authentication failures that have been seen by all the wireless ports.

extremeAPTotalDetectedStations.name: extremeAPTotalDetectedStations
extremeAPTotalDetectedStations.description: This variable gives the total number of detected stations on all the wireless ports.

extremeAPTotalAssociatedStations.name: extremeAPTotalAssociatedStations
extremeAPTotalAssociatedStations.description: This variable gives the total number of associated stations on all the wireless ports.

extremeAPTotalAuthenticatedStations.name: extremeAPTotalAuthenticatedStations
extremeAPTotalAuthenticatedStations.description: This variable gives the total number of authenticated stations on all the wireless ports.

extremeWirelessCfgMgmtVLAN.name: extremeWirelessCfgMgmtVLAN
extremeWirelessCfgMgmtVLAN.description: This value indicates the VLAN tag that should be applied to all control traffic between the AP and the platform.

extremeWirelessCfgNetmask.name: extremeWirelessCfgNetmask
extremeWirelessCfgNetmask.description: This value is the subnet of the Mgmt Vlan

extremeWirelessCfgGateway.name: extremeWirelessCfgGateway
extremeWirelessCfgGateway.description: This value is assigned to the APs as the gateway for the management vlan.

extremeWirelessCfgEnableWirelessTraps.name: extremeWirelessCfgEnableWirelessTraps
extremeWirelessCfgEnableWirelessTraps.description: If set to TRUE the wireless port will send traps for Authentication and association events. If set to FALSE no traps will be generated. Note: We always generate the wireless port status traps.

extremeWirelessCfgCountryCode.name: extremeWirelessCfgCountryCode
extremeWirelessCfgCountryCode.description: This variable allows configuration of the country code in which the AP will operate. Setting this value will enable the AP to range check frequency and other regulatory settings.

extremeWirelessPortCfgTable.name: extremeWirelessPortCfgTable
extremeWirelessPortCfgTable.description: This table contains one entry per wireless port that the user has configured. The AP does not have to be plugged in for the user to configure it via this table.

extremeWirelessPortIfIndex.name: extremeWirelessPortIfIndex
extremeWirelessPortIfIndex.description: This is the MIB-II ifIndex of the port this entry describes.

extremeWirelessPortCfgIpAddress.name: extremeWirelessPortCfgIpAddress
extremeWirelessPortCfgIpAddress.description: This value is assigned to the port for external management.

extremeWirelessPortCfgLocation.name: extremeWirelessPortCfgLocation
extremeWirelessPortCfgLocation.description: This describes the physical location of the wireless port.

extremeWirelessPortCfgDetectedTimeout.name: extremeWirelessPortCfgDetectedTimeout
extremeWirelessPortCfgDetectedTimeout.description: This is the number of seconds a station can stay in the detected station table without authenticating.

extremeWirelessPortCfgClientWatchdog.name: extremeWirelessPortCfgClientWatchdog
extremeWirelessPortCfgClientWatchdog.description: Setting this value to true will force the AP to run a watch-dog process for system health.

extremeWirelessPortLastChange.name: extremeWirelessPortLastChange
extremeWirelessPortLastChange.description: The value of sysUpTime when the port entered its last state

extremeWirelessPortState.name: extremeWirelessPortState
extremeWirelessPortState.description: The current state of the wireless part of this port. enabled : Port is actively looking for wireless interfaces. disabled : Port is administratively unable to detect new interfaces. reset : Interfaces have been detected and are being brought up (access point is booting). addressing : IP Address is being assigned. register : Interfaces are registering for service syncing : Interfaces are retrieving their configuration and updating their state. online : Interfaces are operational. If an error occurs the wireless port will transistion to the error state.

extremeWirelessPortAntennaType.name: extremeWirelessPortAntennaType
extremeWirelessPortAntennaType.description: This is the type of the Antenna for Detachable product. For Altitude-2d series, further selection is available through this variable.

extremeWirelessPortAntennaLocation.name: extremeWirelessPortAntennaLocation
extremeWirelessPortAntennaLocation.description: This specifies the location the detachable antenna.

extremeWirelessPortBootstrapServerAddres.name: extremeWirelessPortBootstrapServerAddressType
extremeWirelessPortBootstrapServerAddres.description: The type of address specified in the object 'extremeWirelessPortBootstrapServerAddress'. Currently, only 'ipv4' and 'dns' are supported.

extremeWirelessPortBootstrapServerAddres.name: extremeWirelessPortBootstrapServerAddress
extremeWirelessPortBootstrapServerAddres.description: This specifies the TFTP server address from where the AP gets the Bootstrap Image. This can be a DNS name or an IPv4 address.

extremeWirelessPortBootstrapFilePath.name: extremeWirelessPortBootstrapFilePath
extremeWirelessPortBootstrapFilePath.description: This specifies the TFTP FileName of the AP Bootstrap Image.

extremeWirelessPortBootLoaderServerAddre.name: extremeWirelessPortBootLoaderServerAddressType
extremeWirelessPortBootLoaderServerAddre.description: The type of address specified in the object 'extremeWirelessPortBootLoaderServerAddress'. Currently, only 'ipv4' and 'dns' are supported.

extremeWirelessPortBootLoaderServerAddre.name: extremeWirelessPortBootLoaderServerAddress
extremeWirelessPortBootLoaderServerAddre.description: This specifies the TFTP server address from where the AP gets the Bootloader Image. This can be a DNS name or an IPv4 address.

extremeWirelessPortBootLoaderFilePath.name: extremeWirelessPortBootLoaderFilePath
extremeWirelessPortBootLoaderFilePath.description: This specifies the TFTP FileName of the AP Bootloader Image.

extremeWirelessPortRuntimeServerAddressT.name: extremeWirelessPortRuntimeServerAddressType
extremeWirelessPortRuntimeServerAddressT.description: The type of address specified in the object 'extremeWirelessPortRuntimeServerAddress'. Currently, only 'ipv4' and 'dns' are supported.

extremeWirelessPortRuntimeServerAddress.name: extremeWirelessPortRuntimeServerAddress
extremeWirelessPortRuntimeServerAddress.description: This specifies the TFTP server address from where the AP gets the Runtime Image. This can be a DNS name or an IPv4 address.

extremeWirelessPortRuntimeFilePath.name: extremeWirelessPortRuntimeFilePath
extremeWirelessPortRuntimeFilePath.description: This specifies the TFTP FileName of the AP Runtime Image.

extremeWirelessPortMultiBootMode.name: extremeWirelessPortMultiBootMode
extremeWirelessPortMultiBootMode.description: This is used to identify the image with which the AP boots up. This is enumerated as follows: 0 - a300 - This specifies that AP will bootup with Extreme's A300 image 1 - a-bp - This specifies that AP will bootup with Siemen''s Beacon Point Image.

extremeWirelessPortStatusTable.name: extremeWirelessPortStatusTable
extremeWirelessPortStatusTable.description: This table contains one entry per detected AP.

extremeWirelessPortIpAddress.name: extremeWirelessPortIpAddress
extremeWirelessPortIpAddress.description: This value is assigned to the port for external management.

extremeWirelessPortNetmask.name: extremeWirelessPortNetmask
extremeWirelessPortNetmask.description: This value is assigned to the AP for external management.

extremeWirelessPortGateway.name: extremeWirelessPortGateway
extremeWirelessPortGateway.description: This value is assigned to the AP for external management.

extremeWirelessPortManagementIP.name: extremeWirelessPortManagementIP
extremeWirelessPortManagementIP.description: This value is used by the AP when sending out Management packets to the external world. This IP is used as src-ip address in Syslog messages, as NAS-Identifier in Radius requests, and as Agent-Addr in SNMP trap pdu's.

extremeWirelessPortEnableWirelessTraps.name: extremeWirelessPortEnableWirelessTraps
extremeWirelessPortEnableWirelessTraps.description: If set to TRUE the wireless port will send traps for Authentication and association successful events. If set to FALSE no traps will be generated. Note: We always generate the wireless port status traps.

extremeWirelessPortLocation.name: extremeWirelessPortLocation
extremeWirelessPortLocation.description: This describes the physical location of the wireless port.

extremeWirelessPortDetectedMaxAge.name: extremeWirelessPortDetectedMaxAge
extremeWirelessPortDetectedMaxAge.description: This is the number of seconds a station can stay in the detected station table without authenticating.

extremeWirelessPortMgmtVLAN.name: extremeWirelessPortMgmtVLAN
extremeWirelessPortMgmtVLAN.description: This value indicates the VLAN tag that should be applied to all control traffic between the AP and the platform.

extremeWirelessPortBootromVersion.name: extremeWirelessPortBootromVersion
extremeWirelessPortBootromVersion.description: This is the current version of the bootrom on this AP.

extremeWirelessPortSWVersion.name: extremeWirelessPortSWVersion
extremeWirelessPortSWVersion.description: This is the current software version of this AP.

extremeWirelessPortSysDescr.name: extremeWirelessPortSysDescr
extremeWirelessPortSysDescr.description: This is the equivalent value of sysDescr from the AP.

extremeWirelessPortSerialNumber.name: extremeWirelessPortSerialNumber
extremeWirelessPortSerialNumber.description: This is the unique serial number for this device.

extremeWirelessPortEdpNeighborId.name: extremeWirelessPortEdpNeighborId
extremeWirelessPortEdpNeighborId.description: EDP assigns a unique ID to each neighbor to disambiguate references. This can be used to index into the extremeEdpTable.

extremeWirelessPortClearCounters.name: extremeWirelessPortClearCounters
extremeWirelessPortClearCounters.description: This value can be set to true to force the device to reset it's counters. A read will return false.

extremeWirelessPortClearLog.name: extremeWirelessPortClearLog
extremeWirelessPortClearLog.description: This value can be set to true to force the device to clear its local log store. A read will return false.

extremeWirelessPortWatchdogReset.name: extremeWirelessPortWatchdogReset
extremeWirelessPortWatchdogReset.description: This is to enable/disable watchdog timer reset on timeout. Default is enable. If it is enabled, system should reset when the watchdog kicks in. On next bootup, it should send out an syslog message to syslog server. If it is disabled, it should record the error and not reset the system.

extremeWirelessPortNumPhysInterfaces.name: extremeWirelessPortNumPhysInterfaces
extremeWirelessPortNumPhysInterfaces.description: Each wireless port has a set of physical interface which are numbered 1-N. This variable gives the number of physical interfaces on this AP.

extremeWirelessPortHWVersion.name: extremeWirelessPortHWVersion
extremeWirelessPortHWVersion.description: This is the current hardware version of this AP.

extremeWirelessPortMacAddress.name: extremeWirelessPortMacAddress
extremeWirelessPortMacAddress.description: Unique MAC Address assigned to the ethernet interface on the AP.

extremeWirelessPortRadiusPortID.name: extremeWirelessPortRadiusPortID
extremeWirelessPortRadiusPortID.description: A string value that should be sent by the AP to the radius server as the Port-ID radius attribute in authentication requests

extremeWirelessPortBootUpTime.name: extremeWirelessPortBootUpTime
extremeWirelessPortBootUpTime.description: The sysUpTime of the LAC when the port was booted up. Should be set only during the AP boot up.

extremeWirelessPortCountryCode.name: extremeWirelessPortCountryCode
extremeWirelessPortCountryCode.description: The country code that the AP is programmed to operate in.

extremeWirelessPortWallclockTime.name: extremeWirelessPortWallclockTime
extremeWirelessPortWallclockTime.description: The wall clock time as known to the LAC. Expressed in number of seconds since Jan 1, 1970

extremeWirelessPortPartNumber.name: extremeWirelessPortPartNumber
extremeWirelessPortPartNumber.description: This describes the part number of the AP.

extremeWirelessPortPartRevision.name: extremeWirelessPortPartRevision
extremeWirelessPortPartRevision.description: This describes the revision of the AP.

extremeWirelessPortUpTime.name: extremeWirelessPortUpTime
extremeWirelessPortUpTime.description: The number of seconds the port has been in the online state.

extremeWirelessPortStatusAntennaType.name: extremeWirelessPortStatusAntennaType
extremeWirelessPortStatusAntennaType.description: This is the type of the Antenna for Detachable product. For Altitude-2d series, further selection is available through this variable.

extremeWirelessPortStatusAntennaLocation.name: extremeWirelessPortStatusAntennaLocation
extremeWirelessPortStatusAntennaLocation.description: This specifies the location the detachable antenna.

extremeWirelessPortStatusAntenna2point4G.name: extremeWirelessPortStatusAntenna2point4GHZGain
extremeWirelessPortStatusAntenna2point4G.description: This specifies 2.4GHz gain value for detachable antenna in dbi

extremeWirelessPortStatusAntenna5GHZGain.name: extremeWirelessPortStatusAntenna5GHZGain
extremeWirelessPortStatusAntenna5GHZGain.description: This specifies 5GHz gain value for detachable antenna in dbi

extremeWirelessPortPrimaryBootloaderVers.name: extremeWirelessPortPrimaryBootloaderVersion
extremeWirelessPortPrimaryBootloaderVers.description: This is the version of the primary bootloader on this AP.

extremeWirelessPortSecondaryBootloaderVe.name: extremeWirelessPortSecondaryBootloaderVersion
extremeWirelessPortSecondaryBootloaderVe.description: This is the version of the Secondary bootloader on this AP.

extremeWirelessPortCurrentBootloaderInUs.name: extremeWirelessPortCurrentBootloaderInUse
extremeWirelessPortCurrentBootloaderInUs.description: This specifies if the bootloader booted is primary or secondary one.

extremeWirelessPortLogStatusTable.name: extremeWirelessPortLogStatusTable
extremeWirelessPortLogStatusTable.description: This table contains one entry for each wireless port which is configured via the configuration table.

extremeWirelessPortLogStatusIndex.name: extremeWirelessPortLogStatusIndex
extremeWirelessPortLogStatusIndex.description: There are 9 entries in this table to correspond to the 8 entries configured in the cfg table plus one for the LAC.

extremeWirelessPortLogStatusDestIp.name: extremeWirelessPortLogStatusDestIp
extremeWirelessPortLogStatusDestIp.description: This is the IP address to which syslog messsages will be sent. A value of 0.0.0.0 indicates that this entry is disabled. The source IP for every syslog message comes from the ManagementIP field in extremeWirelessPortStatusTable

extremeWirelessPortLogStatusDestIpType.name: extremeWirelessPortLogStatusDestIpType
extremeWirelessPortLogStatusDestIpType.description: The type of address specified in the object 'extremeWirelessPortLogStatusDestIp. Currently, only 'ipv4' and 'dns' are supported.

extremeWirelessPortLogStatusPort.name: extremeWirelessPortLogStatusPort
extremeWirelessPortLogStatusPort.description: This is the port to which syslog messages will be sent.

extremeWirelessPortLogStatusFacility.name: extremeWirelessPortLogStatusFacility
extremeWirelessPortLogStatusFacility.description: Optional value for syslog facility local0-7.

extremeWirelessPortLogStatusSeverity.name: extremeWirelessPortLogStatusSeverity
extremeWirelessPortLogStatusSeverity.description: The syslog message severity. All syslog messages that have a severity >= specified severity, will be sent to this syslog server.

extremeWirelessPortLogStatusStatus.name: extremeWirelessPortLogStatusStatus
extremeWirelessPortLogStatusStatus.description: Specifies whether the log server is enabled or not.

extremeWirelessPortLogTable.name: extremeWirelessPortLogTable
extremeWirelessPortLogTable.description: This table allows access to the syslog entries on particular wireless ports.

extremeWirelessPortLogIndex.name: extremeWirelessPortLogIndex
extremeWirelessPortLogIndex.description: This is an arbitrary integer which is assinged to entries in order of their insertion.

extremeWirelessPortLogMessage.name: extremeWirelessPortLogMessage
extremeWirelessPortLogMessage.description: This is the formatted syslog message which was sent.

extremeWirelessPhysInterfaceCtlTable.name: extremeWirelessPhysInterfaceCtlTable
extremeWirelessPhysInterfaceCtlTable.description: This table provides configuration of per-physical interface values.

extremeWirelessPhysInterfaceCtlEntry.name: extremeWirelessPhysInterfaceCtlEntry
extremeWirelessPhysInterfaceCtlEntry.description: Each entry is indexed by the wirelessInterfaceIndex, and represents a wireless interface.

extremeWirelessPhysInterfaceIndex.name: extremeWirelessPhysInterfaceIndex
extremeWirelessPhysInterfaceIndex.description: This is the ifIndex of an individual physical interface on an AP. Each radio will have a unique value.

extremeWirelessPhysInterfacePHYChannel.name: extremeWirelessPhysInterfacePHYChannel
extremeWirelessPhysInterfacePHYChannel.description: This is the RF channel which will be used by this transmitter. Range should be established by configuration of RegDomain and PHYType.

extremeWirelessPhysInterfaceSpeed.name: extremeWirelessPhysInterfaceSpeed
extremeWirelessPhysInterfaceSpeed.description: This value indicates the current setting for Tx speed for the interface. Only one of thebits of this bit set can be set. If all bits are unset (ie a 0 is passed as a value) then it means that the interface should choose a speed based on some algorithm.

extremeWirelessPhysInterfaceNumVirtInter.name: extremeWirelessPhysInterfaceNumVirtInterfaces
extremeWirelessPhysInterfaceNumVirtInter.description: Each physical interface has a number of virtual interfaces This specifies the number of virt interfaces.

extremeWirelessPhysInterfaceChannelAutoS.name: extremeWirelessPhysInterfaceChannelAutoSelectStatus
extremeWirelessPhysInterfaceChannelAutoS.description: This OID reflects the status of the channel auto selection process.

extremeWirelessPhysInterfaceRadarInterfa.name: extremeWirelessPhysInterfaceRadarInterfaceChannelList
extremeWirelessPhysInterfaceRadarInterfa.description: This OID reflects the list oc 802.11(a) channels on which radar interference was detected.

extremeWirelessVirtInterfaceCtlTable.name: extremeWirelessVirtInterfaceCtlTable
extremeWirelessVirtInterfaceCtlTable.description: This table provides configuration of per-physical-interface values.

extremeWirelessVirtInterfaceCtlEntry.name: extremeWirelessVirtInterfaceCtlEntry
extremeWirelessVirtInterfaceCtlEntry.description: Each entry is indexed by the wirelessInterfaceIndex, and represents a virtual wireless interface.

extremeWirelessVirtInterfaceIndex.name: extremeWirelessVirtInterfaceIndex
extremeWirelessVirtInterfaceIndex.description: This is the ifIndex of an individual interface on an AP. Each virtual interface will have a unique value.

extremeWirelessVirtInterfaceMacAddress.name: extremeWirelessVirtInterfaceMacAddress
extremeWirelessVirtInterfaceMacAddress.description: The maximum number of clients that can associate with this virtual interface.

extremeWirelessVirtInterfaceMaxClients.name: extremeWirelessVirtInterfaceMaxClients
extremeWirelessVirtInterfaceMaxClients.description: The maximum number of clients that can associate with this virtual interface.

extremeWirelessVirtInterfaceWirelessBrid.name: extremeWirelessVirtInterfaceWirelessBridging
extremeWirelessVirtInterfaceWirelessBrid.description: This specifies whether wireless bridging is enabled on this interface. If wireless bridging is enabled then traffic originating from a client on this interface will be bridged to clients on the same VLAN on this or other virtual interfaces that have wireless bridging enabled. So basically wireless bridging should be enabled on both the source and the destination virtual interface for traffic to be bridged.

extremeWirelessVirtInterfaceLastStateCha.name: extremeWirelessVirtInterfaceLastStateChange
extremeWirelessVirtInterfaceLastStateCha.description: The value of sysUpTime when the virtual interface entered its current state

extremeWirelessVirtInterfaceState.name: extremeWirelessVirtInterfaceState
extremeWirelessVirtInterfaceState.description: This value specifies whether the virtual interface is active or not

extremeWirelessVirtInterfaceIappEnabled.name: extremeWirelessVirtInterfaceIappEnabled
extremeWirelessVirtInterfaceIappEnabled.description: IAPP status. A value of TRUE indicates IAPP is enabled on the interface.

extremeWirelessVirtInterfaceSvpEnabled.name: extremeWirelessVirtInterfaceSvpEnabled
extremeWirelessVirtInterfaceSvpEnabled.description: SVP status. A value of TRUE indicates SVP is enabled on the interface.

extremeWirelessVirtInterfaceSecurityCtlT.name: extremeWirelessVirtInterfaceSecurityCtlTable
extremeWirelessVirtInterfaceSecurityCtlT.description: This table provides configuration of per-interface values.

extremeWirelessVirtInterfaceSecurityCtlE.name: extremeWirelessVirtInterfaceSecurityCtlEntry
extremeWirelessVirtInterfaceSecurityCtlE.description: Each entry is indexed by the wirelessInterfaceIndex, and represents a wireless interface.

extremeWirelessVirtInterfaceESSName.name: extremeWirelessVirtInterfaceESSName
extremeWirelessVirtInterfaceESSName.description: The ESS ID of this interface.

extremeWirelessVirtInterfaceSSIDInBeacon.name: extremeWirelessVirtInterfaceSSIDInBeacon
extremeWirelessVirtInterfaceSSIDInBeacon.description: Does this interface generate a beacon with the SSID in it?

extremeWirelessVirtInterfaceDot11AuthMod.name: extremeWirelessVirtInterfaceDot11AuthMode
extremeWirelessVirtInterfaceDot11AuthMod.description: Setting this to true indicates whether to use open or shared authentication

extremeWirelessVirtInterfaceNetworkAuthM.name: extremeWirelessVirtInterfaceNetworkAuthMode
extremeWirelessVirtInterfaceNetworkAuthM.description: This specifies the authentication mode to use on top of dot11 MAC authentication

extremeWirelessVirtInterfaceDataVlan.name: extremeWirelessVirtInterfaceDataVlan
extremeWirelessVirtInterfaceDataVlan.description: This is the VLAN to use for client data in case of the VLAN is not received as a VSA. This VLAN is also used for authentication types like PSK, WEP, etc

extremeWirelessVirtInterfaceIgnoreVSAVla.name: extremeWirelessVirtInterfaceIgnoreVSAVlan
extremeWirelessVirtInterfaceIgnoreVSAVla.description: If this is set then the VLAN returned as a VSA will be ignored and the Data Vlan specified above will be used instead

extremeWirelessVirtInterfaceWEPDefaultKe.name: extremeWirelessVirtInterfaceWEPDefaultKey
extremeWirelessVirtInterfaceWEPDefaultKe.description: This value indicates the index in dot11WEPDefaultKeyTable that identifies the key this interface will use to decrypt packets.

extremeWirelessVirtInterfaceEncryptionLe.name: extremeWirelessVirtInterfaceEncryptionLength
extremeWirelessVirtInterfaceEncryptionLe.description: This is the length of the encryption key to use in case of dot1x legacy mode and WEP. If this length is 0 then no WEP encryption.

extremeWirelessVirtInterfaceDot1xCtlTabl.name: extremeWirelessVirtInterfaceDot1xCtlTable
extremeWirelessVirtInterfaceDot1xCtlTabl.description: There is one entry in this table for each virtual interface It reflects the dot1x security config

extremeWirelessVirtInterfaceKeyMgmtSuite.name: extremeWirelessVirtInterfaceKeyMgmtSuite
extremeWirelessVirtInterfaceKeyMgmtSuite.description: This bitmask configures the authentication suites to be used.

extremeWirelessVirtInterfaceMcastCipherS.name: extremeWirelessVirtInterfaceMcastCipherSuite
extremeWirelessVirtInterfaceMcastCipherS.description: This configures the cipher suite to use for mcast traffic. The cipher suite to use for unicast traffic is derived from this using the following algorithm: Mcast cipher = WEP (64/128), Unicast cipher = TKIP Mcast cipher = TKIP, Unicast cipher = TKIP Mcast cipher = AES, Unicast cipher = AES. This therefore determines the max unicast cipher suite the client can use to associate with this interface.

extremeWirelessVirtInterfaceDot1xPSKValu.name: extremeWirelessVirtInterfaceDot1xPSKValue
extremeWirelessVirtInterfaceDot1xPSKValu.description: The Pre-Shared Key (PSK) for when WPA in PSK mode is the selected authentication suite.

extremeWirelessVirtInterfaceDot1xPSKPass.name: extremeWirelessVirtInterfaceDot1xPSKPassPhrase
extremeWirelessVirtInterfaceDot1xPSKPass.description: The PSK, for when WPA in PSK mode is the selected authentication suite, is configured by extremeWirelessVirtInterfaceKeyMgmtSuite. An alternative manner of setting the PSK uses the password-to-key algorithm defined in section XXX. This variable provides a means to enter a pass phrase. When this object is written, the RSN entity shall use the password-to-key algorithm specified in section XXX to derive a pre-shared and populate extremeWirelessVirtInerfaceDot1xPSKValue with this key. This object is logically write-only. Reading this variable shall return unsuccessful status or null or zero.

extremeWirelessVirtInterfaceDot1xReAuthP.name: extremeWirelessVirtInterfaceDot1xReAuthPeriod
extremeWirelessVirtInterfaceDot1xReAuthP.description: Number of seconds a clients authentication will last before the AP automatically issues a reauthentication request.

extremeWirelessVirtInterfaceGroupUpdateT.name: extremeWirelessVirtInterfaceGroupUpdateTimeOut
extremeWirelessVirtInterfaceGroupUpdateT.description: The time in minutes after which the RSN group update handshake will be retried. The timer shall start at the moment the group update message is sent.

extremeWirelessVirtInterfacePairwiseUpda.name: extremeWirelessVirtInterfacePairwiseUpdateTimeOut
extremeWirelessVirtInterfacePairwiseUpda.description: The time in minutes after which the RSN 4-way handshake will be retried. The timer shall start at the moment a 4-way message is sent.

extremeWirelessVirtInterfaceWEPKeyTable.name: extremeWirelessVirtInterfaceWEPKeyTable
extremeWirelessVirtInterfaceWEPKeyTable.description: This table contains per-profile WEP keys. Reference ieee802dot11.1.2.3.

extremeWirelessVirtInterfaceWEPKeyIndex.name: extremeWirelessVirtInterfaceWEPKeyIndex
extremeWirelessVirtInterfaceWEPKeyIndex.description: There can be upto 4 wep keys for any wireless interface. Four of the keys are to be used with WEP Authentication, and the other four with MAC Auth.

extremeWirelessVirtInterfaceWEPKey.name: extremeWirelessVirtInterfaceWEPKey
extremeWirelessVirtInterfaceWEPKey.description: This is a write-only wep key.

extremeWirelessVirtInterfaceWEPKeyStatus.name: extremeWirelessVirtInterfaceWEPKeyStatus
extremeWirelessVirtInterfaceWEPKeyStatus.description: Specifies whether the key is present or not.

extremeWirelessPhysInterfaceRFCtlTable.name: extremeWirelessPhysInterfaceRFCtlTable
extremeWirelessPhysInterfaceRFCtlTable.description: This table provides configuration of per-interface values.

extremeWirelessPhysInterfaceRFCtlEntry.name: extremeWirelessPhysInterfaceRFCtlEntry
extremeWirelessPhysInterfaceRFCtlEntry.description: Each entry is indexed by the wirelessInterfaceIndex, and represents a wireless interface.

extremeWirelessPhysInterfaceBeaconPeriod.name: extremeWirelessPhysInterfaceBeaconPeriod
extremeWirelessPhysInterfaceBeaconPeriod.description: This is the beacon interval to use

extremeWirelessPhysInterfaceTxPowerLevel.name: extremeWirelessPhysInterfaceTxPowerLevel
extremeWirelessPhysInterfaceTxPowerLevel.description: This is the % of max power to transmit at.

extremeWirelessPhysInterfaceLongRetry.name: extremeWirelessPhysInterfaceLongRetry
extremeWirelessPhysInterfaceLongRetry.description: Attribute indicates the maximum number of transmission attempts of a frame whose size is > RTS.

extremeWirelessPhysInterfaceShortRetry.name: extremeWirelessPhysInterfaceShortRetry
extremeWirelessPhysInterfaceShortRetry.description: Attribute indicates the maximum number of transmission attempts of a frame whose size is <= RTS.

extremeWirelessPhysInterfaceSupportedDat.name: extremeWirelessPhysInterfaceSupportedDataRatesRxValue
extremeWirelessPhysInterfaceSupportedDat.description: A bitmask of all supported datarates for Rx.

extremeWirelessPhysInterfaceSupportedDat.name: extremeWirelessPhysInterfaceSupportedDataRatesTxValue
extremeWirelessPhysInterfaceSupportedDat.description: A bitmask of all supported datarates for Tx.

extremeWirelessPhysInterfacePHYType.name: extremeWirelessPhysInterfacePHYType
extremeWirelessPhysInterfacePHYType.description: This variable selects between 802.11 a/b/g for this transmitter. It should be used by ap to range check frequency, etc.

extremeWirelessPhysInterfacePHYSupported.name: extremeWirelessPhysInterfacePHYSupportedTypes
extremeWirelessPhysInterfacePHYSupported.description: This is the 802.11 standard supported by this interface as a bitmask

extremeWirelessPhysInterfacePreamble.name: extremeWirelessPhysInterfacePreamble
extremeWirelessPhysInterfacePreamble.description: This changes the 802 preamble expected by the interface.

extremeWirelessPhysInterfaceAbsTxPowerLe.name: extremeWirelessPhysInterfaceAbsTxPowerLevel
extremeWirelessPhysInterfaceAbsTxPowerLe.description: This is the absolute value of max power to transmit level in dBm.

extremeWirelessInterfaceStatusTable.name: extremeWirelessInterfaceStatusTable
extremeWirelessInterfaceStatusTable.description: This table provides statistics and information on the current condition of each wireless interace. There is one entry per virtual and physical wireless interface in this table. The values for the physical interfaces represent the sum of the values for all sub interfaces.

extremeWirelessInterfaceStatusEntry.name: extremeWirelessInterfaceStatusEntry
extremeWirelessInterfaceStatusEntry.description: Each entry in this table is indexed by either a virtual or a physical ifIndex.

extremeWirelessIntfTotalDetected.name: extremeWirelessIntfTotalDetected
extremeWirelessIntfTotalDetected.description: This gives the total number of stations which have entered the detected state on this wireless interface since the last time the counters were cleared.

extremeWirelessIntfTotalAuthed.name: extremeWirelessIntfTotalAuthed
extremeWirelessIntfTotalAuthed.description: This gives the total number of stations which have entered the authenticated state on this wireless interface since the last time the counters were cleared. Note that this is equal to the number of stations which have entered the forwarding state. This is not necessaryly equivalent to the number of stations which have succeeded in MAC-level authentication.

extremeWirelessIntfTotalAuthFailed.name: extremeWirelessIntfTotalAuthFailed
extremeWirelessIntfTotalAuthFailed.description: This gives the total number of stations which have failed to authenticate on this wireless interface. Note that no distinction is made between a MAC-layer or higher-layer authentication failure.

extremeWirelessIntfTotalAssoc.name: extremeWirelessIntfTotalAssoc
extremeWirelessIntfTotalAssoc.description: This gives the total number of stations which have entered the associated state on this wireless interface since the last time the counters were cleared.

extremeWirelessIntfTotalAssocFailed.name: extremeWirelessIntfTotalAssocFailed
extremeWirelessIntfTotalAssocFailed.description: This gives the total number of stations which have failed the association on this wireless interface since the last time the counters were cleared.

extremeWirelessIntfRateDetected.name: extremeWirelessIntfRateDetected
extremeWirelessIntfRateDetected.description: This gives the rate of clients being detected on this interface over a 5 second period using EMWA averaging.

extremeWirelessIntfRateAuthed.name: extremeWirelessIntfRateAuthed
extremeWirelessIntfRateAuthed.description: This gives teh rate of clients being authenticated on this interface over a 5 second period using EMWA averaging.

extremeWirelessIntfRateAuthFailed.name: extremeWirelessIntfRateAuthFailed
extremeWirelessIntfRateAuthFailed.description: This gives the rate of clients failed authentication on this interface over a 5 second period using EMWA averaging.

extremeWirelessIntfRateAssoc.name: extremeWirelessIntfRateAssoc
extremeWirelessIntfRateAssoc.description: This gives the rate of clients being associated on this interface over a 5 second period using EMWA averaging.

extremeWirelessIntfRateAssocFailed.name: extremeWirelessIntfRateAssocFailed
extremeWirelessIntfRateAssocFailed.description: This gives the rate of clients failing association on this interface over a 5 second period using EMWA averaging.

extremeWirelessIntfBlockTime.name: extremeWirelessIntfBlockTime
extremeWirelessIntfBlockTime.description: This value specifies the number of ticks until traffic will be allowed back on this interface. A non-zero value indicates that traffic has been blocked, most likely due to countermeasures.

extremeWirelessIntfCurrentDetected.name: extremeWirelessIntfCurrentDetected
extremeWirelessIntfCurrentDetected.description: This gives the current number of stations which are in the detected state on this wireless interface.

extremeWirelessIntfCurrentAuthed.name: extremeWirelessIntfCurrentAuthed
extremeWirelessIntfCurrentAuthed.description: This gives the current number of stations which are in the authenticated state on this wireless interface.

extremeWirelessIntfCurrentAssoc.name: extremeWirelessIntfCurrentAssoc
extremeWirelessIntfCurrentAssoc.description: This gives the current number of stations which are in the associated state on this wireless interface.

extremeWirelessIntfCurrentForwarding.name: extremeWirelessIntfCurrentForwarding
extremeWirelessIntfCurrentForwarding.description: This gives the current number of stations which are in the forwarding state on this wireless interface.

extremeWirelessClientTable.name: extremeWirelessClientTable
extremeWirelessClientTable.description: This table augments the Dot11AccessPointAddressTableEntry to add a per-client VLAN entry.

extremeWirelessClientEntry.name: extremeWirelessClientEntry
extremeWirelessClientEntry.description: An entry in the extremeWirelessClientTable. It is possible for there to be multiple IEEE 802.11 interfaces on one agent, each with its unique MAC address. The relationship between an IEEE 802.11 interface and an interface in the context of the Internet-standard MIB is one-to-one. As such, the value of an ifIndex object instance can be directly used to identify corresponding instances of the objects defined herein. by ifIndex.

extremeWirelessClientID.name: extremeWirelessClientID
extremeWirelessClientID.description: The Unique MAC Address of the station for which this address table entry pertains.

extremeWirelessClientState.name: extremeWirelessClientState
extremeWirelessClientState.description: This attribute shall indicate the current state of the connection between a wireless station and the AP. The attribute is enumerated as follows: 1 - Detected - station has been detected, but not is communicating with AP 2 - Authenticated - station is authenticated but not currently associated. 3 - Associated - station is authenticated and associated 4 - Data-forwarding - station is on the network It is assumed that if an station is deauthenticated, or disassociated then it no longer has an entry the AP's Address Table.

extremeWirelessClientEncryption.name: extremeWirelessClientEncryption
extremeWirelessClientEncryption.description: This attribute is contains the encryption mechanism being used by the station in an AP that allows mixed encryption modes.

extremeWirelessClientSignalStrength.name: extremeWirelessClientSignalStrength
extremeWirelessClientSignalStrength.description: This attribute shall specify the signal strength of the last frame received from the station in - dBm. e.g. a value of 50 implies -50 dBm.

extremeWirelessClientLinkQuality.name: extremeWirelessClientLinkQuality
extremeWirelessClientLinkQuality.description: This attribute shall contain an indication of the quality of the signal as measured in the last frame received from the station. TBD format of this attribute

extremeWirelessClientVLAN.name: extremeWirelessClientVLAN
extremeWirelessClientVLAN.description: This is the per-client VLAN which was pushed over by a RADIUS server or other mechanism.

extremeWirelessClientPriority.name: extremeWirelessClientPriority
extremeWirelessClientPriority.description: This is a per-client 802.1p value which was either configured by the RADIUS server or statically through the port configuration table.

extremeWirelessClientAuthType.name: extremeWirelessClientAuthType
extremeWirelessClientAuthType.description: This is an indication of what access method was used to authenticated the client. The strongest mechanism used should be listed here, in case more than one was used. For example, if a combination of mac-based shared-key and dot1x were used, this value should indicated dot1x.

extremeWirelessClientLastStateChangeTime.name: extremeWirelessClientLastStateChangeTime
extremeWirelessClientLastStateChangeTime.description: This is the sysUpTime of the switch when the clients state changed last

extremeWirelessClientTxFrames.name: extremeWirelessClientTxFrames
extremeWirelessClientTxFrames.description: This is the number of packets transmitted to the client

extremeWirelessClientRxFrames.name: extremeWirelessClientRxFrames
extremeWirelessClientRxFrames.description: This is the number of packets transmitted by the client

extremeWirelessClientTxBytes.name: extremeWirelessClientTxBytes
extremeWirelessClientTxBytes.description: This is the number of bytes transmitted to the client

extremeWirelessClientRxBytes.name: extremeWirelessClientRxBytes
extremeWirelessClientRxBytes.description: This is the number of bytes transmitted by the client

extremeWirelessClientLastPacketType.name: extremeWirelessClientLastPacketType
extremeWirelessClientLastPacketType.description: This the the last packet type seen from the specific client

extremeWirelessClientSSID.name: extremeWirelessClientSSID
extremeWirelessClientSSID.description: The SSID that this client was using

extremeWirelessClientStatus.name: extremeWirelessClientStatus
extremeWirelessClientStatus.description: This variable is used to delete an entry from the table. The only value this can be set to, is delete (6). If an entry is deleted, that is already in Associated or data-forwarding state, then the AP should dis-associate the particular client by sending a disassociate message. If an entry is in Authenticated state, and is deleted, then the AP should 'deAuthenticate' that client. If an entry is in 'detected' state and is deleted, then the entry should just be removed from the table.

extremeWirelessClientIP.name: extremeWirelessClientIP
extremeWirelessClientIP.description: IP Address of the wireless client.

extremeWirelessClientUsername.name: extremeWirelessClientUsername
extremeWirelessClientUsername.description: Username (if any) of the wireless client.

extremeWirelessClientDecryptionFailures.name: extremeWirelessClientDecryptionFailures
extremeWirelessClientDecryptionFailures.description: This is the number of failures during decrypting packets from this client.

extremeWirelessClientMICFailures.name: extremeWirelessClientMICFailures
extremeWirelessClientMICFailures.description: This is the number of MIC failures for this client.

extremeRFProfileTable.name: extremeRFProfileTable
extremeRFProfileTable.description: There is one entry in this table for each RF profile defined on the LAC. Configuration for wireless intf. should only be done by manipulating these variables. Changes here will be reflected in the corresponding 802dot11 MIB variables (see references below). On bootup this table should be populated with one default entry for each supported type (A, G, etc).

extremeRFProfileIndex.name: extremeRFProfileIndex
extremeRFProfileIndex.description: Integer index for this table. This is here to avoid having to index into the table via the string name.

extremeRFProfileName.name: extremeRFProfileName
extremeRFProfileName.description: String name of this profile. The value |default| is a special token and should not be allowed.

extremeRFProfileType.name: extremeRFProfileType
extremeRFProfileType.description: This is the type of this RF profile. This will decide the ranges of some of the values (i.e. channel).

extremeRFProfileBeaconInterval.name: extremeRFProfileBeaconInterval
extremeRFProfileBeaconInterval.description: This is the number of TU between beacon frames.

extremeRFProfilePreamble.name: extremeRFProfilePreamble
extremeRFProfilePreamble.description: This changes the 802 preamble expected by the interface.

extremeRFProfileShortRetry.name: extremeRFProfileShortRetry
extremeRFProfileShortRetry.description: Attribute indicates the maximum number of transmission attempts of a frame whose size is <= RTS.

extremeRFProfileLongRetry.name: extremeRFProfileLongRetry
extremeRFProfileLongRetry.description: Attribute indicates the maximum number of transmission attempts of a frame whose size is > RTS.

extremeSecurityProfileTable.name: extremeSecurityProfileTable
extremeSecurityProfileTable.description: There is one entry in this table per security profile on the LAC. Each profile is identified by a string name.

extremeSecurityProfileIndex.name: extremeSecurityProfileIndex
extremeSecurityProfileIndex.description: This is an integer index used instead of string name.

extremeSecurityProfileName.name: extremeSecurityProfileName
extremeSecurityProfileName.description: This is a unique string name which identifies this profile. The token |default| is special and should not be allowed.

extremeSecurityProfileESSName.name: extremeSecurityProfileESSName
extremeSecurityProfileESSName.description: This is the desired ESS name.

extremeSecurityProfileSSIDInBeacon.name: extremeSecurityProfileSSIDInBeacon
extremeSecurityProfileSSIDInBeacon.description: Setting this value to true will have the channel place the ssid in the beacon frame.

extremeSecurityProfileDot11AuthMode.name: extremeSecurityProfileDot11AuthMode
extremeSecurityProfileDot11AuthMode.description: Specified whether to use open or shared authentication

extremeSecurityProfileNetworkAuthMode.name: extremeSecurityProfileNetworkAuthMode
extremeSecurityProfileNetworkAuthMode.description: This specifies the authentication to use on top of dot11 mac authentication

extremeSecurityProfileDataVlan.name: extremeSecurityProfileDataVlan
extremeSecurityProfileDataVlan.description: This specifies the VLAN to use in case it does not come back as a VSA or in case the IgnoreVSAVlan is set to true

extremeSecurityProfileIgnoreVSAVlan.name: extremeSecurityProfileIgnoreVSAVlan
extremeSecurityProfileIgnoreVSAVlan.description: This specifies if Vlan associations in VSAs from the radius server has to be ignored or not

extremeSecurityWEPDefaultKey.name: extremeSecurityWEPDefaultKey
extremeSecurityWEPDefaultKey.description: This value indicates the index in extremeWEPKeyTable that identifies the key this interface will use to decrypt packets.

extremeSecurityProfileEncryptionLength.name: extremeSecurityProfileEncryptionLength
extremeSecurityProfileEncryptionLength.description: This gives the size in bits of the key. This variable defines the length of all WEP keys and also the encryption to use in case of legacy dot1x. If the encryption is set to none then no WEP encryption is set.

extremeSecurityDot1xConfigTable.name: extremeSecurityDot1xConfigTable
extremeSecurityDot1xConfigTable.description: There is one entry in this table per security profile on the LAC. It reflects the dot1x security config

extremeSecurityKeyMgmtSuite.name: extremeSecurityKeyMgmtSuite
extremeSecurityKeyMgmtSuite.description: This bitmask configures the authentication suites to be used.

extremeSecurityMcastCipherSuite.name: extremeSecurityMcastCipherSuite
extremeSecurityMcastCipherSuite.description: This configures the cipher suite to use for mcast traffic. The cipher suite to use for unicast traffic is derived from this using the following algorithm: Mcast cipher = WEP (64/128), Unicast cipher = TKIP Mcast cipher = TKIP, Unicast cipher = TKIP Mcast cipher = AES, Unicast cipher = AES. This therefore determines the max unicast cipher suite the client can use to associate with this interface.

extremeSecurityDot1xPSKValue.name: extremeSecurityDot1xPSKValue
extremeSecurityDot1xPSKValue.description: The Pre-Shared Key (PSK) for when RSN in PSK mode is the selected authentication suite.

extremeSecurityDot1xPSKPassPhrase.name: extremeSecurityDot1xPSKPassPhrase
extremeSecurityDot1xPSKPassPhrase.description: The PSK, for when WPA in PSK mode is the selected authentication suite, is configured by extremeSecurityKeyMgmtSuite. An alternative manner of setting the PSK uses the password-to-key algorithm defined in section XXX. This variable provides a means to enter a pass phrase. When this object is written, the RSN entity shall use the password-to-key algorithm specified in section XXX to derive a pre-shared and populate extremeSecurityDot1xPSKValue with this key. This object is logically write-only. Reading this variable shall return unsuccessful status or null or zero.

extremeSecurityDot1xReAuthPeriod.name: extremeSecurityDot1xReAuthPeriod
extremeSecurityDot1xReAuthPeriod.description: Number of seconds a clients authentication will last before the AP automatically issues a reauthentication request.

extremeSecurityGroupUpdateTimeOut.name: extremeSecurityGroupUpdateTimeOut
extremeSecurityGroupUpdateTimeOut.description: The time in minutes after which the RSN group update handshake will be retried. The timer shall start at the moment the group update message is sent.

extremeSecurityPairwiseUpdateTimeOut.name: extremeSecurityPairwiseUpdateTimeOut
extremeSecurityPairwiseUpdateTimeOut.description: The time in minutes after which the RSN 4-way handshake will be retried. The timer shall start at the moment a 4-way message is sent.

extremeSecurityDot11iPreauthEnabled.name: extremeSecurityDot11iPreauthEnabled
extremeSecurityDot11iPreauthEnabled.description: Whether preauth is enabled or not

extremeWEPKeyTable.name: extremeWEPKeyTable
extremeWEPKeyTable.description: This table contains per-profile WEP keys. Reference ieee802dot11.1.2.3.

extremeWEPKeyIndex.name: extremeWEPKeyIndex
extremeWEPKeyIndex.description: There can be upto 8 wep keys for any wireless interface. Four of the keys are to be used with WEP Authentication, and the other four with MAC Auth.

extremeWEPKey.name: extremeWEPKey
extremeWEPKey.description: This is a write-only wep key.

extremeWirelessPhysInterfaceConfigTable.name: extremeWirelessPhysInterfaceConfigTable
extremeWirelessPhysInterfaceConfigTable.description: This table contains the configured bindings between physical wireless interfaces and RF profiles and other RF properties. There is one instance of a physical wireless interface per radio on the AP. Entries in this table have a duration that exceeds the lifetime of entries in the wirelessPhysInterfaceCtlTable. A configured binding spans the reset or removal of a wireless interface. Entries can be removed from this table by the user. If there is a mismatch between a new wireless port and a previously configured profile, the default profile will be applied and this table will be updated.

extremeWirelessPhysInterfaceConfigRFProf.name: extremeWirelessPhysInterfaceConfigRFProfile
extremeWirelessPhysInterfaceConfigRFProf.description: This is the index into the extremeRFProfileTable for the RF profile that this wireless interface is bound to. The default value is equivalent to the profile index for the interface-appropriate default in the table.

extremeWirelessPhysInterfaceConfigRFChan.name: extremeWirelessPhysInterfaceConfigRFChannel
extremeWirelessPhysInterfaceConfigRFChan.description: This is the RF channel which has been selected for this wireless interface. It should be one of the supported channels as given by the phy tables in the dot11 mib.

extremeWirelessPhysInterfaceConfigSpeed.name: extremeWirelessPhysInterfaceConfigSpeed
extremeWirelessPhysInterfaceConfigSpeed.description: This is the speed to configure the interface at. A value of 0 indicates automatic speed detection.

extremeWirelessPhysInterfaceConfigPowerL.name: extremeWirelessPhysInterfaceConfigPowerLevel
extremeWirelessPhysInterfaceConfigPowerL.description: This value specifies the tx power (in % of max power) to use.

extremeWirelessVirtInterfaceConfigTable.name: extremeWirelessVirtInterfaceConfigTable
extremeWirelessVirtInterfaceConfigTable.description: This table contains the configured bindings between virtual wireless interfaces and security profiles and other security properties. There are upto 8 virtual interface for each physical interface. Entries in this table have a duration that exceeds the lifetime of entries in the wirelessVirtInterfaceCtlTable. A configured binding spans the reset or removal of a wireless interface. Entries can be removed from this table by the user.

extremeWirelessVirtInterfaceConfigSecuri.name: extremeWirelessVirtInterfaceConfigSecurityProfile
extremeWirelessVirtInterfaceConfigSecuri.description: This is the index into the extremeSecurityProfileTable for the security profile that this wireless interface is bound to. The default value is equivalent to the profile index for the interface-appropriate default in the table.

extremeWirelessVirtInterfaceConfigMaxCli.name: extremeWirelessVirtInterfaceConfigMaxClients
extremeWirelessVirtInterfaceConfigMaxCli.description: The maximum number of clients that can associate with this virtual interface.

extremeWirelessVirtInterfaceConfigWirele.name: extremeWirelessVirtInterfaceConfigWirelessBridging
extremeWirelessVirtInterfaceConfigWirele.description: This specifies whether wireless bridging is enabled on this interface. If wireless bridging is enabled then traffic originating from a client on this interface will be bridged to clients on the same VLAN on this or other virtual interfaces that have wireless bridging enabled. So basically wireless bridging should be enabled on both the source and the destination virtual interface for traffic to be bridged.

extremeWirelessVirtInterfaceConfigState.name: extremeWirelessVirtInterfaceConfigState
extremeWirelessVirtInterfaceConfigState.description: This value specifies whether the virtual interface is active or not

extremeAntennaProfileTable.name: extremeAntennaProfileTable
extremeAntennaProfileTable.description: There is one entry in this table per antenna profile on the LAC. Each profile is identified by a string name.

extremeAntennaProfileIndex.name: extremeAntennaProfileIndex
extremeAntennaProfileIndex.description: This is an integer index used instead of string name.

extremeAntennaProfileName.name: extremeAntennaProfileName
extremeAntennaProfileName.description: This is a unique string name which identifies this profile. The token |default| is special and should not be allowed.

extremeAntennaProfile2point4GHZGain.name: extremeAntennaProfile2point4GHZGain
extremeAntennaProfile2point4GHZGain.description: This specifies 2.4GHz gain value for detachable antenna in dbi

extremeAntennaProfile5GHZGain.name: extremeAntennaProfile5GHZGain
extremeAntennaProfile5GHZGain.description: This specifies 5GHz gain value for detachable antenna in dbi

extremeWirelessRemoteConnectBindingTable.name: extremeWirelessRemoteConnectBindingTable
extremeWirelessRemoteConnectBindingTable.description: This table specifies the RemoteConnect binding configuration for various ports.

extremeWirelessRemoteConnectBindingPortI.name: extremeWirelessRemoteConnectBindingPortIndex
extremeWirelessRemoteConnectBindingPortI.description: The index of this binding. This maps one-to-one with the value specified in the CLI. For example, if you say v:1 in the CLI, then this value should be 1.

extremeWirelessRemoteConnectBindingIfInd.name: extremeWirelessRemoteConnectBindingIfIndex
extremeWirelessRemoteConnectBindingIfInd.description: This is the IF index that is used in the extremeWirelessPortConfigTable etc to refer to this RemoteConnect port.

extremeWirelessRemoteConnectBindingType.name: extremeWirelessRemoteConnectBindingType
extremeWirelessRemoteConnectBindingType.description: This is the type of binding. Based on this, one of the following columns will be valid.

extremeWirelessRemoteConnectBindingMAC.name: extremeWirelessRemoteConnectBindingMAC
extremeWirelessRemoteConnectBindingMAC.description: The MAC address of the AP that is bound to this virtual port. This is valid only if the extremeWirelessRemoteConnectBindingType is set to mac-address

extremeWirelessRemoteConnectBindingSeria.name: extremeWirelessRemoteConnectBindingSerial
extremeWirelessRemoteConnectBindingSeria.description: The serial number of the AP that is bound to this virtual port. This is valid only if the extremeWirelessRemoteConnectBindingType is set to serial-number

extremeWirelessRemoteConnectBindingIPAdd.name: extremeWirelessRemoteConnectBindingIPAddressType
extremeWirelessRemoteConnectBindingIPAdd.description: The IP address type of the AP that is bound to this virtual port. This is valid only if the extremeWirelessRemoteConnectBindingType is set to ip-address

extremeWirelessRemoteConnectBindingIPAdd.name: extremeWirelessRemoteConnectBindingIPAddress
extremeWirelessRemoteConnectBindingIPAdd.description: The IP address of the AP that is bound to this virtual port. This is valid only if the extremeWirelessRemoteConnectBindingType is set to ip-address

extremeWirelessRemoteConnectBindingEnabl.name: extremeWirelessRemoteConnectBindingEnabled
extremeWirelessRemoteConnectBindingEnabl.description: An entry in this table can be created but left as disabled. If you set this variable to True then the RemoteConnect controller will consider this binding when trying to map APs to RemoteConnect ports. Else, it will ignore it.

extremeWirelessRemoteConnectBindingBound.name: extremeWirelessRemoteConnectBindingBound
extremeWirelessRemoteConnectBindingBound.description: Specifies if an AP has come up and has been matched to this binding. If this is true, then the extremeWirelessPortStatus table will have an entry for this RemoteConnect port.

extremeWirelessRemoteConnectBindingRowSt.name: extremeWirelessRemoteConnectBindingRowStatus
extremeWirelessRemoteConnectBindingRowSt.description: RowStatus attribute. When this row is deleted, the binding goes away

extremeWirelessRemoteConnectRedirectBind.name: extremeWirelessRemoteConnectRedirectBindingTable
extremeWirelessRemoteConnectRedirectBind.description: This table specifies the RemoteConnect redirection configuration for various ports.

extremeWirelessRemoteConnectRedirectBind.name: extremeWirelessRemoteConnectRedirectBindingType
extremeWirelessRemoteConnectRedirectBind.description: This is the type of RedirectBinding. Based on this, one of the following columns will be valid.

extremeWirelessRemoteConnectRedirectBind.name: extremeWirelessRemoteConnectRedirectBindingMAC
extremeWirelessRemoteConnectRedirectBind.description: The MAC address of the AP that will be redirected. This is valid only if the extremeWirelessRemoteConnectRedirectBindingType is set to mac-address

extremeWirelessRemoteConnectRedirectBind.name: extremeWirelessRemoteConnectRedirectBindingSerial
extremeWirelessRemoteConnectRedirectBind.description: The serial number of the AP that is bound to this virtual port. This is valid only if the extremeWirelessRemoteConnectRedirectBindingType is set to serial-number

extremeWirelessRemoteConnectRedirectBind.name: extremeWirelessRemoteConnectRedirectBindingIPAddressType
extremeWirelessRemoteConnectRedirectBind.description: The IP address type of the AP that will be redirected. This is valid only if the extremeWirelessRemoteConnectRedirectBindingType is set to ip-address

extremeWirelessRemoteConnectRedirectBind.name: extremeWirelessRemoteConnectRedirectBindingIPAddress
extremeWirelessRemoteConnectRedirectBind.description: The IP address of the AP that will be redirected. This is valid only if the extremeWirelessRemoteConnectRedirectBindingType is set to ip-address

extremeWirelessRemoteConnectRedirectBind.name: extremeWirelessRemoteConnectRedirectBindAttachSwitchIPAddrType
extremeWirelessRemoteConnectRedirectBind.description: The IP address type of the slave

extremeWirelessRemoteConnectRedirectBind.name: extremeWirelessRemoteConnectRedirectBindAttachSwitchIPAddr
extremeWirelessRemoteConnectRedirectBind.description: The IP address of the slave

extremeWirelessRemoteConnectRedirectBind.name: extremeWirelessRemoteConnectRedirectBindingEnabled
extremeWirelessRemoteConnectRedirectBind.description: An entry in this table can be created but left as disabled. If you set this variable to True then the RemoteConnect controller will consider this RedirectBinding when trying to redirect APs. Else, it will ignore it.

extremeWirelessRemoteConnectRedirectBind.name: extremeWirelessRemoteConnectRedirectBindingNumRedirects
extremeWirelessRemoteConnectRedirectBind.description: The number of times this redirect has been invoked.

extremeWirelessRemoteConnectDeviceDBTime.name: extremeWirelessRemoteConnectDeviceDBTimeOut
extremeWirelessRemoteConnectDeviceDBTime.description: Timeout value for unbound APs entry in seconds. 0 for disable

extremeWirelessRemoteConnectUnboundAPsTa.name: extremeWirelessRemoteConnectUnboundAPsTable
extremeWirelessRemoteConnectUnboundAPsTa.description: This table contains the list of APs that could not be bound or redirected.

extremeWirelessRemoteConnectUnboundAPsMA.name: extremeWirelessRemoteConnectUnboundAPsMAC
extremeWirelessRemoteConnectUnboundAPsMA.description: The MAC address of the unbound AP.

extremeWirelessRemoteConnectUnboundAPsSe.name: extremeWirelessRemoteConnectUnboundAPsSerial
extremeWirelessRemoteConnectUnboundAPsSe.description: The serial number of the unbound AP

extremeWirelessRemoteConnectUnboundAPsIP.name: extremeWirelessRemoteConnectUnboundAPsIPAddressType
extremeWirelessRemoteConnectUnboundAPsIP.description: The IP address type of the unbound AP

extremeWirelessRemoteConnectUnboundAPsIP.name: extremeWirelessRemoteConnectUnboundAPsIPAddress
extremeWirelessRemoteConnectUnboundAPsIP.description: The IP address of the unbound AP

extremeWirelessRemoteConnectUnboundAPsNu.name: extremeWirelessRemoteConnectUnboundAPsNumAttempts
extremeWirelessRemoteConnectUnboundAPsNu.description: The number of times this AP contacted this controller.

extremeWirelessRemoteConnectUnboundAPsRo.name: extremeWirelessRemoteConnectUnboundAPsRowStatus
extremeWirelessRemoteConnectUnboundAPsRo.description: Standard row status semantics. Only valid value to set is destroy (6).

extremeAPAuthServerTable.name: extremeAPAuthServerTable
extremeAPAuthServerTable.description: This table is proxied by the wireless APs. It allows the wireless concentrator to configure the APs security settings.

extremeAPAuthServerIndex.name: extremeAPAuthServerIndex
extremeAPAuthServerIndex.description: Integer representing either primary (1) or backup (2) server.

extremeAPAuthServerAddressType.name: extremeAPAuthServerAddressType
extremeAPAuthServerAddressType.description: The type of address specified in the object 'extremeAuthServerAddress'. Currently, only 'ipv4' and 'dns' are supported.

extremeAPAuthServerAddress.name: extremeAPAuthServerAddress
extremeAPAuthServerAddress.description: IP address of the radius server. The act of assigning an IP address enables the client to use the server. Setting this value to 0.0.0.0 disables this entry.

extremeAPAuthServerPort.name: extremeAPAuthServerPort
extremeAPAuthServerPort.description: The UDP port number of the remote syslog server to which syslog messages will be sent.

extremeAPAuthServerSecret.name: extremeAPAuthServerSecret
extremeAPAuthServerSecret.description: This is the shared secret between the Authenticator and radius server. This is logically write-only.

extremeAPAuthServerReTransmit.name: extremeAPAuthServerReTransmit
extremeAPAuthServerReTransmit.description: This is the timeout in seconds after which the Authenticator will re transmit requests to the radius server.

extremeAPAuthServerStatus.name: extremeAPAuthServerStatus
extremeAPAuthServerStatus.description: Specifies whether the DNS entry is in use or not

extremeWirelessScanCfgTable.name: extremeWirelessScanCfgTable
extremeWirelessScanCfgTable.description: This table contains one entry per wireless interface. It allows for configuration of active and passive scan parameters.

extremeWirelessScanEnable.name: extremeWirelessScanEnable
extremeWirelessScanEnable.description: By setting this to true the wireless interface will collect information from beacons and (possible) probe responses. If this value is set to false this information will not be collected.

extremeWirelessScanSendProbe.name: extremeWirelessScanSendProbe
extremeWirelessScanSendProbe.description: If this value is set to TRUE the wireless interface will send probe requests to the broadcast SSID every ProbeInterval. The results of these probes will be recorded in the scan results table. If this is false, the AP will only collect information from beacon frames.

extremeWirelessScanProbeInterval.name: extremeWirelessScanProbeInterval
extremeWirelessScanProbeInterval.description: This allows for the configuration of the interval over which probe requests will be sent.

extremeWirelessScanResultTableSize.name: extremeWirelessScanResultTableSize
extremeWirelessScanResultTableSize.description: This parameter permits the configuration of the result table size. If there are more entries discovered than there are room for the new entry will replace the oldest entry in the table. In this case a new entry trap will be sent with the OverFlow value set to TRUE.

extremeWirelessScanResultTimeout.name: extremeWirelessScanResultTimeout
extremeWirelessScanResultTimeout.description: By default the scan result table will age out entries which haven't been updated for some time. When an entry is aged out of the table a scanResultAgeOut trap is generated. Setting this value to 0 will disable the aging out of entries.

extremeWirelessScanResetStats.name: extremeWirelessScanResetStats
extremeWirelessScanResetStats.description: Setting this to TRUE will cause the scan module to reset its internal statistics, as well as the packet counts for each entry in the scan results table. It will *not* remove any entries in the scan table.

extremeWirelessScanClearTable.name: extremeWirelessScanClearTable
extremeWirelessScanClearTable.description: Setting this to TRUE will cause the scan module to reset its internal table. All currently detected stations will be removed. Scan statistics (i.e. watermark) will not be reset.

extremeWirelessScanSendAPAddedTrap.name: extremeWirelessScanSendAPAddedTrap
extremeWirelessScanSendAPAddedTrap.description: Setting this to TRUE will cause the scan module to send a trap whenever a new entry is added to the scan results table. If this value is false the scan module will suppress the trap.

extremeWirelessScanSendAPRemovedTrap.name: extremeWirelessScanSendAPRemovedTrap
extremeWirelessScanSendAPRemovedTrap.description: Setting this to TRUE will cause the scan module to send a trap whenever an entry is removed from the scan results table.

extremeWirelessScanSendAPUpdatedTrap.name: extremeWirelessScanSendAPUpdatedTrap
extremeWirelessScanSendAPUpdatedTrap.description: Setting this to TRUE will cause the scan module to send a trap whenever an entry is updated in the scan results table. This will happen if the list of IEs sent from a particular MAC address changes.

extremeWirelessOffChannelScanCfgTable.name: extremeWirelessOffChannelScanCfgTable
extremeWirelessOffChannelScanCfgTable.description: This table contains one entry per wireless interface. It allows for configuration of off-channel scan. To start an off-channel scan the management station should write values for channel list, min and max wait. Toggling the start value at this point will start an off-channel scan, unless one is already running. Results of the off-channel scan are reported to the scan results table together with the results of passive scan.

extremeWirelessOffChannelScanStart.name: extremeWirelessOffChannelScanStart
extremeWirelessOffChannelScanStart.description: Setting this to TRUE will cause the scan module to start an off-channel scan. The radio will be disabled for the duration of the scan. The scan module will change to each of the specified channels in order. It will then conduct passive (and perhaps active) scans on that channel for the configured intervals. When the scan is finished the radio will be re-enabled. The scan will wait on each channel for at least MinWait milliseconds even if it sees no traffic on the channel. It will wait for at most MaxWait msecs even if it sees traffic. As a result the best case time for the scan is given by: # Of Channels * extremeWirelessOffChannelScanMinWait The worst case completion time is given by: # Of Channels * extremeWirelessOffChannelScanMaxWait Results of the off-channnel scan a reported to the scan results table.

extremeWirelessOffChannelScanList.name: extremeWirelessOffChannelScanList
extremeWirelessOffChannelScanList.description: This value controls the channels which will be scanned during the off-channel scan. Two special values should be noted: all - causes the radio to scan all channels supported by the configured country code. While on each channel the radio will send out probe requests if the value of extremeWirelessScanSendProbeRequest is true. every - causes the radio to scan all channels, even those which are restricted by the country code. The radio will only send probe request on channels that are legal for that country code.

extremeWirelessOffChannelScanMinWait.name: extremeWirelessOffChannelScanMinWait
extremeWirelessOffChannelScanMinWait.description: This value controls the minimum time the off-channel scan will wait on a particular channel if it doesn't see any traffic.

extremeWirelessOffChannelScanMaxWait.name: extremeWirelessOffChannelScanMaxWait
extremeWirelessOffChannelScanMaxWait.description: This value controls the maximum time the off-channel scan will wait on a particular channel even if it is receiving beacons etc.

extremeWirelessOffChannelContinuous.name: extremeWirelessOffChannelContinuous
extremeWirelessOffChannelContinuous.description: Setting this value to true results in the off-channel scan looping on the configured values until the channel scan is disabled.

extremeWirelessScanStatusTable.name: extremeWirelessScanStatusTable
extremeWirelessScanStatusTable.description: This table contains one entry per wireless interface. It provides status and statistics information for the scan feature operating on that wireless interface.

extremeWirelessScanCurrentTableSize.name: extremeWirelessScanCurrentTableSize
extremeWirelessScanCurrentTableSize.description: This indicates the current number of entries in the scan results table.

extremeWirelessScanTableWatermark.name: extremeWirelessScanTableWatermark
extremeWirelessScanTableWatermark.description: This indicates the largest size the results table has reached since the status values have been reset, or the system has booted.

extremeWirelessScanTotalOverflows.name: extremeWirelessScanTotalOverflows
extremeWirelessScanTotalOverflows.description: This gives the total number of entries which have been removed to make room for a newer entry. This should be equal to the number of AP added traps the system has generated with the overflow value set to true.

extremeWirelessScanTotalTimeouts.name: extremeWirelessScanTotalTimeouts
extremeWirelessScanTotalTimeouts.description: This gives the total number of entries which have been removed because they have become stale. This should be equal to the number of AP removed traps sent by the system.

extremeWirelessScanOffChannelRunning.name: extremeWirelessScanOffChannelRunning
extremeWirelessScanOffChannelRunning.description: If this value is true it indicates that an off-channel scan is currently running. This implies that the radio is current disabled.

extremeWirelessScanCurrentChannel.name: extremeWirelessScanCurrentChannel
extremeWirelessScanCurrentChannel.description: If the value of extremeWirelessScanOffChannelRunning is true this variable give the value of the current channel the AP is scanning on. If a scan is not running, the value of this variable is undefined.

extremeWirelessScanLastElement.name: extremeWirelessScanLastElement
extremeWirelessScanLastElement.description: This gives the sysUpTime when the last new station was inserted in the results table.

extremeWirelessScanNumProbes.name: extremeWirelessScanNumProbes
extremeWirelessScanNumProbes.description: This gives the number of probe requests sent by this wireless interface.

extremeWirelessScanResultsTable.name: extremeWirelessScanResultsTable
extremeWirelessScanResultsTable.description: This table contains one entry per wireless interface. It provides status and statistics information for the scan feature operating on that wireless interface.

extremeWirelessScanResultsStationId.name: extremeWirelessScanResultsStationId
extremeWirelessScanResultsStationId.description: This is the MAC address of the detected station.

extremeWirelessScanResultsFirstSeen.name: extremeWirelessScanResultsFirstSeen
extremeWirelessScanResultsFirstSeen.description: This gives the sysUpTime when this station entry was created.

extremeWirelessScanResultsLastChange.name: extremeWirelessScanResultsLastChange
extremeWirelessScanResultsLastChange.description: This gives the sysUpTime of the station entry the last time it was updated (i.e. a beacon etc was received).

extremeWirelessScanResultsPacketTime.name: extremeWirelessScanResultsPacketTime
extremeWirelessScanResultsPacketTime.description: This gives the timestamp field from the last beacon/probe response received from this station.

extremeWirelessScanResultsPacketRate.name: extremeWirelessScanResultsPacketRate
extremeWirelessScanResultsPacketRate.description: This gives the rate at which the last packet was sent by the station. TODO: What are the units here on rate?

extremeWirelessScanResultsChannel.name: extremeWirelessScanResultsChannel
extremeWirelessScanResultsChannel.description: This gives the channel the last packet received by this station was recieved on.

extremeWirelessScanResultsMinRSS.name: extremeWirelessScanResultsMinRSS
extremeWirelessScanResultsMinRSS.description: This is the smallest RSS value of any packet recieved from this station.

extremeWirelessScanResultsMaxRSS.name: extremeWirelessScanResultsMaxRSS
extremeWirelessScanResultsMaxRSS.description: This is the largest RSS value of any packet recieved from this station.

extremeWirelessScanResultsAvgRSS.name: extremeWirelessScanResultsAvgRSS
extremeWirelessScanResultsAvgRSS.description: This is a running average of RSS values of all the packets received from this station.

extremeWirelessScanResultsTotalBeacons.name: extremeWirelessScanResultsTotalBeacons
extremeWirelessScanResultsTotalBeacons.description: This counter gives the total number of beacons received from this station.

extremeWirelessScanResultsTotalProbes.name: extremeWirelessScanResultsTotalProbes
extremeWirelessScanResultsTotalProbes.description: This counter gives the total number of probe responses received from this station.

extremeWirelessScanResultsDiscoveredBy.name: extremeWirelessScanResultsDiscoveredBy
extremeWirelessScanResultsDiscoveredBy.description: This gives the type of packet which cause this results entry to be created.

extremeWirelessScanResultsRSNEnabled.name: extremeWirelessScanResultsRSNEnabled
extremeWirelessScanResultsRSNEnabled.description: Indicates if RSN capabilities are enabled on the sending station.

extremeWirelessScanResultsPrivacy.name: extremeWirelessScanResultsPrivacy
extremeWirelessScanResultsPrivacy.description: This is true if MAC-based privacy is invoked on the sending station.

extremeWirelessScanResultsNetworkType.name: extremeWirelessScanResultsNetworkType
extremeWirelessScanResultsNetworkType.description: This indicates what type of network it is. If this value is IBSS the last beacon/probe response was sent by a host operating in ad-hoc mode.

extremeWirelessScanResultsSSID.name: extremeWirelessScanResultsSSID
extremeWirelessScanResultsSSID.description: This provides the value of the SSID value as is was recieved in the beacon or probe response. If no SSID was sent in the probe this value is NULL.

extremeWirelessScanResultsRateSet.name: extremeWirelessScanResultsRateSet
extremeWirelessScanResultsRateSet.description: This provides the value of the rate set IE as it was received in the beacon or probe response. If no rate set was recieved then this value is NULL.

extremeWirelessScanResultsExtRateSet.name: extremeWirelessScanResultsExtRateSet
extremeWirelessScanResultsExtRateSet.description: This provides the value of the extended rate set IE as it was received in the beacon or probe response. If no rate set was recieved then this value is NULL.

extremeWirelessScanResultsDSSParameter.name: extremeWirelessScanResultsDSSParameter
extremeWirelessScanResultsDSSParameter.description: Provides the value of the DSS parameter IE, which is the channel.

extremeWirelessScanResultsCountryCode.name: extremeWirelessScanResultsCountryCode
extremeWirelessScanResultsCountryCode.description: Value of country code supplied by the IE

extremeWirelessScanWPAIEPresent.name: extremeWirelessScanWPAIEPresent
extremeWirelessScanWPAIEPresent.description: If this value is true it indicates that WPA information was gathered from this AP in the last beacon. It implies that the WPA variables below are valid. If this value is false it indicates that this AP did not send a WPA IE in its last beacon, and the values below are meaningless.

extremeWirelessScanWPAVersion.name: extremeWirelessScanWPAVersion
extremeWirelessScanWPAVersion.description: This value gives the version of WPA supported by this AP. See IEEE 802.11i Draft 3.0 section 7 for meaning of various values.

extremeWirelessScanWPAIEMcastCipher.name: extremeWirelessScanWPAIEMcastCipher
extremeWirelessScanWPAIEMcastCipher.description: This value gives the single multicast cipher supported by this AP.

extremeWirelessScanWPAUcastCipherCount.name: extremeWirelessScanWPAUcastCipherCount
extremeWirelessScanWPAUcastCipherCount.description: This value gives the total number of unicast ciphers supported by this AP. It corresponds to the number of bits set in the extremeWirelessScanWPAUcastCipher variable.

extremeWirelessScanWPAUcastCipher.name: extremeWirelessScanWPAUcastCipher
extremeWirelessScanWPAUcastCipher.description: This gives the list of cipher suites which are supported by this AP.

extremeWirelessScanWPAKeyMgmtCount.name: extremeWirelessScanWPAKeyMgmtCount
extremeWirelessScanWPAKeyMgmtCount.description: This gives the number of key-management schemes supported by this AP. It corresponds to the number of bits set in the extremeWirelessScanWPAKeyMgmtSuite variable.

extremeWirelessScanWPAKeyMgmtSuite.name: extremeWirelessScanWPAKeyMgmtSuite
extremeWirelessScanWPAKeyMgmtSuite.description: This indicates the supported key-management suites supported by this AP.

extremeWirelessScanResultsIEBlob.name: extremeWirelessScanResultsIEBlob
extremeWirelessScanResultsIEBlob.description: All the IEs received in the last packet encoded as a blob of Type, Length, Value tuples.

extremeWirelessProbeInfoCfgTable.name: extremeWirelessProbeInfoCfgTable
extremeWirelessProbeInfoCfgTable.description: This table contains one entry per physical and virtual interface. It controls the collection of client information via PROBE REQ packets.

extremeWirelessProbeInfoCfgEntry.name: extremeWirelessProbeInfoCfgEntry
extremeWirelessProbeInfoCfgEntry.description: Note that the ifIndex here can be either a physical or virtual wireless interface index.

extremeWirelessProbeInfoEnable.name: extremeWirelessProbeInfoEnable
extremeWirelessProbeInfoEnable.description: If this is set to TRUE then this virtual or physical interface will register with the MAC layer to receive notification of PROBE REQ packets. In the case of a virtual interface this implies the receipt of directed PROBE REQ packets. If set to FALSE no PROBE REQ packets will be received, and current entries will eventually timeout.

extremeWirelessProbeInfoKeepIEs.name: extremeWirelessProbeInfoKeepIEs
extremeWirelessProbeInfoKeepIEs.description: If this value is set to TRUE then the rate IE which is carried in the PROBE REQ packet will be recorded. If FALSE, no rate information will be kept.

extremeWirelessProbeInfoTableSize.name: extremeWirelessProbeInfoTableSize
extremeWirelessProbeInfoTableSize.description: This value sets the maximum size of the probe info results table, which limits the number of clients this AP can record PROBE REQ information from.

extremeWirelessProbeInfoTimeout.name: extremeWirelessProbeInfoTimeout
extremeWirelessProbeInfoTimeout.description: This is the timeout, in seconds, for an entry in the probe info table. Once a PROBE REQ has not been heard from a client in this time period, it's entry is removed. The value 0 is a sentinel, indicating no timeout.

extremeWirelessProbeInfoTableClear.name: extremeWirelessProbeInfoTableClear
