extremeWirelessProbeInfoTableClear.description: Setting this value to TRUE causes all entries in the probe info table to be removed. Reading this value has no meaning.

extremeWirelessProbeInfoSourceClear.name: extremeWirelessProbeInfoSourceClear
extremeWirelessProbeInfoSourceClear.description: Setting this to the value of some MAC address results in any matching MAC address in the probe info table being removed. Reading this value has no meaning.

extremeWirelessProbeInfoTableStatsClear.name: extremeWirelessProbeInfoTableStatsClear
extremeWirelessProbeInfoTableStatsClear.description: Setting this to TRUE results in all historical statistics in the probe info table being set to 0. No entries will be removed. Reading this has no meaning.

extremeWirelessProbeInfoSourceStatsClear.name: extremeWirelessProbeInfoSourceStatsClear
extremeWirelessProbeInfoSourceStatsClear.description: Setting this to a MAC address will clear the historical stats associated with the matching MAC address in the probe info table. Reading this has no meaning.

extremeWirelessProbeInfoSendAddedTrap.name: extremeWirelessProbeInfoSendAddedTrap
extremeWirelessProbeInfoSendAddedTrap.description: Setting this to TRUE will cause the management module to send a trap whenever a new PROBE REQ source is added to the probe info table. Setting this to FALSE will suppress the trap.

extremeWirelessProbeInfoSendRemovedTrap.name: extremeWirelessProbeInfoSendRemovedTrap
extremeWirelessProbeInfoSendRemovedTrap.description: Setting this to TRUE will cause the management module to send a trap whenever a PROBE REQ source is removed from the probe info table. Setting this to false will suppress the trap.

extremeWirelessProbeInfoStatusTable.name: extremeWirelessProbeInfoStatusTable
extremeWirelessProbeInfoStatusTable.description: This table contains one entry per physical and virtual interface. It gives debugging and status information for the operation of the probe info feature on that interface.

extremeWirelessProbeInfoStatusEntry.name: extremeWirelessProbeInfoStatusEntry
extremeWirelessProbeInfoStatusEntry.description: Note that the ifIndex here can be either a physical or virtual wireless interface index.

extremeWirelessProbeInfoStatusCurrentTab.name: extremeWirelessProbeInfoStatusCurrentTableSize
extremeWirelessProbeInfoStatusCurrentTab.description: This gives the current number of entries in the probe info table for this interface.

extremeWirelessProbeInfoStatusWatermark.name: extremeWirelessProbeInfoStatusWatermark
extremeWirelessProbeInfoStatusWatermark.description: This is the maximum size the probe info table has been since the statistics have been reset.

extremeWirelessProbeInfoStatusTotalOverf.name: extremeWirelessProbeInfoStatusTotalOverflows
extremeWirelessProbeInfoStatusTotalOverf.description: This gives the number of times an entry in the probe info table was overwritten because the table was full.

extremeWirelessProbeInfoStatusTotalTimeo.name: extremeWirelessProbeInfoStatusTotalTimeouts
extremeWirelessProbeInfoStatusTotalTimeo.description: This gives the number of times an entry in the probe info table was timed out.

extremeWirelessProbeInfoStatusLastElemen.name: extremeWirelessProbeInfoStatusLastElement
extremeWirelessProbeInfoStatusLastElemen.description: This gives the sysUpTime the last time an entry was added to the probe info table (or modified).

extremeWirelessProbeInfoStatusTotalProbe.name: extremeWirelessProbeInfoStatusTotalProbes
extremeWirelessProbeInfoStatusTotalProbe.description: This gives the total number of PROBE REQ packets that this interface has gotten.

extremeWirelessProbeInfoTable.name: extremeWirelessProbeInfoTable
extremeWirelessProbeInfoTable.description: This table contains one entry for each source MAC from which a PROBE REQ packet has been received. Entries are added when a packet is recieved from a new source mac. Entries are removed via management action, or by timeout or overflow.

extremeWirelessProbeInfoEntry.name: extremeWirelessProbeInfoEntry
extremeWirelessProbeInfoEntry.description: Note that the ifIndex here can be either a physical or virtual wireless interface index. In addition, this table is indexed by the MAC address of the PROBE REQ source.

extremeWirelessProbeInfoSource.name: extremeWirelessProbeInfoSource
extremeWirelessProbeInfoSource.description: This is the MAC address of the source which sent us the PROBE REQ packets described by this entry.

extremeWirelessProbeInfoTotalProbes.name: extremeWirelessProbeInfoTotalProbes
extremeWirelessProbeInfoTotalProbes.description: This gives the total number of PROBE REQ packets we have received from this source since the last time the stats were cleared.

extremeWirelessProbeInfoTotalProbeResp.name: extremeWirelessProbeInfoTotalProbeResp
extremeWirelessProbeInfoTotalProbeResp.description: This gives the total number of PROBE RESP packets we have sent to this source. This may not be equal to PROBE REQ based on rxmit, misses, etc.

extremeWirelessProbeInfoRateIESize.name: extremeWirelessProbeInfoRateIESize
extremeWirelessProbeInfoRateIESize.description: This gives the size of the rate-ie field in bytes. This may be 0, at which point there is no rate-ie.

extremeWirelessProbeInfoRateIE.name: extremeWirelessProbeInfoRateIE
extremeWirelessProbeInfoRateIE.description: This gives the rate IE as recieved in the last PROBE REQ packet. It is encoded as a TLV exactly as it was in the frame. This field may return NULL if storing of rate IE fields is disabled.

extremeWirelessProbeInfoFirstSeen.name: extremeWirelessProbeInfoFirstSeen
extremeWirelessProbeInfoFirstSeen.description: This gives the sysUpTime the first time a PROBE REQ was seen from this source.

extremeWirelessProbeInfoLastChange.name: extremeWirelessProbeInfoLastChange
extremeWirelessProbeInfoLastChange.description: This gives the sysUpTime the last time a PROBE REQ was seen from this source.

extremeWirelessProbeInfoLastRSS.name: extremeWirelessProbeInfoLastRSS
extremeWirelessProbeInfoLastRSS.description: This gives the RSSI from the last PROBE REQ packet received from this station.

extremeWirelessProbeInfoLastRate.name: extremeWirelessProbeInfoLastRate
extremeWirelessProbeInfoLastRate.description: This gives the rate at which the last packet was received from this station.

extremeWirelessProbeInfoLastChannel.name: extremeWirelessProbeInfoLastChannel
extremeWirelessProbeInfoLastChannel.description: This gives the channel on which the last PROBE REQ from this station was heard. PROBE REQs may be heard during an off-channel scan, at which point this may not be equal to the current channel.

extremeWirelessClientDiagCfgTable.name: extremeWirelessClientDiagCfgTable
extremeWirelessClientDiagCfgTable.description: This table contains one row per wireless interface. Each row contains configuration values for collection of per-client diagnostic information.

extremeWirelessClientDiagCfgEntry.name: extremeWirelessClientDiagCfgEntry
extremeWirelessClientDiagCfgEntry.description: There is one entry in this table per virtual interface (SSID).

extremeWirelessClientDiagCfgEnable.name: extremeWirelessClientDiagCfgEnable
extremeWirelessClientDiagCfgEnable.description: Setting this to TRUE enables the collection of historical information on this virtual interface. This implies that stations which send ASSOC or AUTH packets will have new entries created in the table for this interface.

extremeWirelessClientDiagCfgClearClient.name: extremeWirelessClientDiagCfgClearClient
extremeWirelessClientDiagCfgClearClient.description: Setting this to the MAC address of a client in the diag tables will clear the counters for that client. The entry will not be removed from the table, but all summation counters will be cleared.

extremeWirelessClientDiagCfgTableSize.name: extremeWirelessClientDiagCfgTableSize
extremeWirelessClientDiagCfgTableSize.description: This value will configure the maximum size of the diag table. The value is specified in number of entries. A value of 0 implies no upper limit.

extremeWirelessClientDiagCfgTimeout.name: extremeWirelessClientDiagCfgTimeout
extremeWirelessClientDiagCfgTimeout.description: This value will configure the timeout of an entry from the diagnostics tables. The value is given in seconds. A value of 0 implies no timeout.

extremeWirelessClientDiagStatusTable.name: extremeWirelessClientDiagStatusTable
extremeWirelessClientDiagStatusTable.description: This table contains one entry per virtual interface. Values stored here give current status of the historical client diag feature.

extremeWirelessClientDiagStatusEntry.name: extremeWirelessClientDiagStatusEntry
extremeWirelessClientDiagStatusEntry.description: Note that ifIndex here is virtual ifIndex (SSID).

extremeWirelessClientDiagCurrentTableSiz.name: extremeWirelessClientDiagCurrentTableSize
extremeWirelessClientDiagCurrentTableSiz.description: This is the current size, in entries of the client diag tables.

extremeWirelessClientDiagTableWatermark.name: extremeWirelessClientDiagTableWatermark
extremeWirelessClientDiagTableWatermark.description: This is the maximum size the client diag table has been since the last time the statistics were cleared.

extremeWirelessClientDiagTotalOverflows.name: extremeWirelessClientDiagTotalOverflows
extremeWirelessClientDiagTotalOverflows.description: This is the total number of times an entry has been replaced by a newer entry because there was no room left in the table.

extremeWirelessClientDiagTotalTimeouts.name: extremeWirelessClientDiagTotalTimeouts
extremeWirelessClientDiagTotalTimeouts.description: This is the total number of times an entry has been aged-out of the table.

extremeWirelessClientDiagLastElement.name: extremeWirelessClientDiagLastElement
extremeWirelessClientDiagLastElement.description: This is sysUpTime when the last entry was added to the table.

extremeWirelessClientDiagSupportsSpeedCo.name: extremeWirelessClientDiagSupportsSpeedCounters
extremeWirelessClientDiagSupportsSpeedCo.description: This value indicates if this AP supports the speed-based counters from the extremeWirelessClientSpeedCountersTable.

extremeWirelessClientDiagSupportsSizeCou.name: extremeWirelessClientDiagSupportsSizeCounters
extremeWirelessClientDiagSupportsSizeCou.description: This value indicates if this AP supports the size-based counters from the extremeWirelessClientMACSizeCounterTable.

extremeWirelessClientDiagSupportsPacketC.name: extremeWirelessClientDiagSupportsPacketCounters
extremeWirelessClientDiagSupportsPacketC.description: This value indicates if this AP supports the packet-based counters from the extremeWirelessClientPacketCountersTable.

extremeWirelessClientDiagTable.name: extremeWirelessClientDiagTable
extremeWirelessClientDiagTable.description: This table contains information on a per-client basis. Rows are indexed first by virtual interface, then by client MAC.

extremeWirelessClientDiagEntry.name: extremeWirelessClientDiagEntry
extremeWirelessClientDiagEntry.description: Note that ifIndex here is virtual ifIndex (SSID).

extremeWirelessClientDiagMac.name: extremeWirelessClientDiagMac
extremeWirelessClientDiagMac.description: This is the MAC address of the station this entry describes.

extremeWirelessClientDiagStateWatermark.name: extremeWirelessClientDiagStateWatermark
extremeWirelessClientDiagStateWatermark.description: This is the highest state this client has been in.

extremeWirelessClientDiagEntersInDetecte.name: extremeWirelessClientDiagEntersInDetected
extremeWirelessClientDiagEntersInDetecte.description: This is the total number of times the client has entered the detected state.

extremeWirelessClientDiagErrorsInDetecte.name: extremeWirelessClientDiagErrorsInDetected
extremeWirelessClientDiagErrorsInDetecte.description: This is the total number of errors this client has experienced since the counters were cleared.

extremeWirelessClientDiagAuthReqInDetect.name: extremeWirelessClientDiagAuthReqInDetected
extremeWirelessClientDiagAuthReqInDetect.description: This is the total number of AUTH REQ packets received from this client while it was in the detected state.

extremeWirelessClientDiagOtherReqInDetec.name: extremeWirelessClientDiagOtherReqInDetected
extremeWirelessClientDiagOtherReqInDetec.description: This is the total number of REQ packets received from this client while it was in detected state that were not AUTH REQ packets.

extremeWirelessClientDiagMgmtActionInDet.name: extremeWirelessClientDiagMgmtActionInDetected
extremeWirelessClientDiagMgmtActionInDet.description: This is the total number of times management initiated action (i.e. force-disassociate) was received for this client in the detected state.

extremeWirelessClientDiagTimeOutInDetect.name: extremeWirelessClientDiagTimeOutInDetected
extremeWirelessClientDiagTimeOutInDetect.description: This is the total number of timeouts which happened to this client in the detected state.

extremeWirelessClientDiagEntersInAuth.name: extremeWirelessClientDiagEntersInAuth
extremeWirelessClientDiagEntersInAuth.description: This is the total number of times the client has entered the AUTHED state.

extremeWirelessClientDiagErrorsInAuth.name: extremeWirelessClientDiagErrorsInAuth
extremeWirelessClientDiagErrorsInAuth.description: This is the total number of times the client has had errors in the AUTHED state.

extremeWirelessClientDiagAssocReqInAuth.name: extremeWirelessClientDiagAssocReqInAuth
extremeWirelessClientDiagAssocReqInAuth.description: This is the total number of ASSOC REQ or REASSOC REQ packets received from this client while in the AUTHED state.

extremeWirelessClientDiagOtherReqInAuth.name: extremeWirelessClientDiagOtherReqInAuth
extremeWirelessClientDiagOtherReqInAuth.description: This is the total number of non-ASSOC/REASSOC packets received from this client while in the AUTHED state.

extremeWirelessClientDiagMgmtActionInAut.name: extremeWirelessClientDiagMgmtActionInAuth
extremeWirelessClientDiagMgmtActionInAut.description: This is the total number of management initiated action which this client experienced while in the AUTHED state.

extremeWirelessClientDiagTimeOutInAuth.name: extremeWirelessClientDiagTimeOutInAuth
extremeWirelessClientDiagTimeOutInAuth.description: This is the total number of times this client timed out while in the authed state.

extremeWirelessClientDiagEntersInAssoc.name: extremeWirelessClientDiagEntersInAssoc
extremeWirelessClientDiagEntersInAssoc.description: This is the total number of times this client has entered the associated state.

extremeWirelessClientDiagErrorsInAssoc.name: extremeWirelessClientDiagErrorsInAssoc
extremeWirelessClientDiagErrorsInAssoc.description: This is the total number of errors this client has had in the associated state.

extremeWirelessClientDiagMgmtActionInAss.name: extremeWirelessClientDiagMgmtActionInAssoc
extremeWirelessClientDiagMgmtActionInAss.description: This is the total number of management actions which have happened to this client in the associated state.

extremeWirelessClientDiagTimeOutInAssoc.name: extremeWirelessClientDiagTimeOutInAssoc
extremeWirelessClientDiagTimeOutInAssoc.description: This is the total number of times this station has been timed-out in the associated state.

extremeWirelessClientDiagEntersInForward.name: extremeWirelessClientDiagEntersInForward
extremeWirelessClientDiagEntersInForward.description: This is the total number of times this client has entered the forwarding state.

extremeWirelessClientDiagMgmtActionInFor.name: extremeWirelessClientDiagMgmtActionInForward
extremeWirelessClientDiagMgmtActionInFor.description: This is the total number of times this client has experience a management action while in forwarding.

extremeWirelessClientDiagTimeOutInForwar.name: extremeWirelessClientDiagTimeOutInForward
extremeWirelessClientDiagTimeOutInForwar.description: This is the total number of timeouts this client has experienced while in forwarding.

extremeWirelessClientDiagTotal802Auths.name: extremeWirelessClientDiagTotal802Auths
extremeWirelessClientDiagTotal802Auths.description: This is the total number of times this client has tried to authenticate using 802.1x.

extremeWirelessClientDiagTotalNetLoginAu.name: extremeWirelessClientDiagTotalNetLoginAuths
extremeWirelessClientDiagTotalNetLoginAu.description: This is the total number of times this client has tried to authenticate using NetLogin.

extremeWirelessClientAssocInfoTable.name: extremeWirelessClientAssocInfoTable
extremeWirelessClientAssocInfoTable.description: This table contains one row per client on a wireless interface. It gives information about the association history and parameters of that client.

extremeWirelessClientAssocInfoEntry.name: extremeWirelessClientAssocInfoEntry
extremeWirelessClientAssocInfoEntry.description: Note that ifIndex here is virtual ifIndex (SSID).

extremeWirelessClientAssocInfoAssociated.name: extremeWirelessClientAssocInfoAssociated
extremeWirelessClientAssocInfoAssociated.description: This gives the current MAC-layer association status of this client.

extremeWirelessClientAssocInfoTotalAssoc.name: extremeWirelessClientAssocInfoTotalAssocReq
extremeWirelessClientAssocInfoTotalAssoc.description: This gives the total number of ASSOC REQ pdus recieved from this client since the last time the counters were cleared.

extremeWirelessClientAssocInfoTotalReAss.name: extremeWirelessClientAssocInfoTotalReAssocReq
extremeWirelessClientAssocInfoTotalReAss.description: This gives the total number of REASSOC REQ PDUs received from this client since the last time the counters were cleared.

extremeWirelessClientAssocInfoTotalAssoc.name: extremeWirelessClientAssocInfoTotalAssocResp
extremeWirelessClientAssocInfoTotalAssoc.description: This gives the total number of ASSOC RESP pdus sent to this client since the last time the counters were cleared.

extremeWirelessClientAssocInfoTotalAssoc.name: extremeWirelessClientAssocInfoTotalAssocOK
extremeWirelessClientAssocInfoTotalAssoc.description: This gives the total number of ASSOC RESP PDUs which carried a status = ok response.

extremeWirelessClientAssocInfoTotalAssoc.name: extremeWirelessClientAssocInfoTotalAssocFail
extremeWirelessClientAssocInfoTotalAssoc.description: This gives the total number of ASSOC RESP PDUs which carried a status = failed response.

extremeWirelessClientAssocInfoTotalDisas.name: extremeWirelessClientAssocInfoTotalDisassocReq
extremeWirelessClientAssocInfoTotalDisas.description: This gives the total number of ASSOC RESP PDUs which carried a status = failed response.

extremeWirelessClientAssocInfoTotalDisas.name: extremeWirelessClientAssocInfoTotalDisassocResp
extremeWirelessClientAssocInfoTotalDisas.description: This gives the total number of ASSOC RESP PDUs which carried a status = failed response.

extremeWirelessClientAssocInfoRateIE.name: extremeWirelessClientAssocInfoRateIE
extremeWirelessClientAssocInfoRateIE.description: This is the value of the rate IE carried in the last ASSOC REQ packet if this wireless interface is configured to keep IEs. If it's not, this will be NULL. The IE is encoded as a series of bytes exactly as the value portion of the IE in the PDU.

extremeWirelessClientAssocInfoLastAssoc.name: extremeWirelessClientAssocInfoLastAssoc
extremeWirelessClientAssocInfoLastAssoc.description: This is sysUpTime when the last ASSOC REQ was received from this client.

extremeWirelessClientAssocInfoLastError.name: extremeWirelessClientAssocInfoLastError
extremeWirelessClientAssocInfoLastError.description: This is sysUpTime when the last ASSOC RESP was sent to this client with a failure status.

extremeWirelessClientAssocInfoLastErrorT.name: extremeWirelessClientAssocInfoLastErrorType
extremeWirelessClientAssocInfoLastErrorT.description: This is an enumerated type which indicates which was the last error this client experienced during association.

extremeWirelessClientAssocInfoErrorRateM.name: extremeWirelessClientAssocInfoErrorRateMismatch
extremeWirelessClientAssocInfoErrorRateM.description: This is the total number of failed associations due to a mismatch of the rate IEs.

extremeWirelessClientAssocInfoErrorBadSt.name: extremeWirelessClientAssocInfoErrorBadState
extremeWirelessClientAssocInfoErrorBadSt.description: This is the total number of failed associations due to the client being in the wrong state.

extremeWirelessClientAssocInfoErrorBadCa.name: extremeWirelessClientAssocInfoErrorBadCapability
extremeWirelessClientAssocInfoErrorBadCa.description: This is the total number of failed associations due to the client having a capability mismatch with the AP.

extremeWirelessClientAssocInfoErrorCount.name: extremeWirelessClientAssocInfoErrorCounterMeasure
extremeWirelessClientAssocInfoErrorCount.description: This is the total number of failed associations due to the client being subject to a counter measure.

extremeWirelessClientAssocInfoErrorMcast.name: extremeWirelessClientAssocInfoErrorMcastCipher
extremeWirelessClientAssocInfoErrorMcast.description: This is the total number of failed associations due to the client not supporting the current multicast cipher.

extremeWirelessClientAssocInfoErrorMaxAs.name: extremeWirelessClientAssocInfoErrorMaxAssoc
extremeWirelessClientAssocInfoErrorMaxAs.description: This is the total number of failed associations due to the AP having too many associations already.

extremeWirelessClientAssocInfoErrorRSNRe.name: extremeWirelessClientAssocInfoErrorRSNRequired
extremeWirelessClientAssocInfoErrorRSNRe.description: This is the total number of failed associations due to the client not supplying the (required) RSN IE.

extremeWirelessClientAssocInfoErrorRSNMi.name: extremeWirelessClientAssocInfoErrorRSNMismatch
extremeWirelessClientAssocInfoErrorRSNMi.description: This is the total number of failed associations due to the client's RSN IE not matching supported features on the AP.

extremeWirelessClientAssocInfoErrorOther.name: extremeWirelessClientAssocInfoErrorOther
extremeWirelessClientAssocInfoErrorOther.description: This is the total number of failed associations due to the client's RSN IE not matching supported features on the AP.

extremeWirelessClientAssocInfoWPAIEPrese.name: extremeWirelessClientAssocInfoWPAIEPresent
extremeWirelessClientAssocInfoWPAIEPrese.description: If this value is true it indicates that WPA information was gathered from this station in the last association request. If true, it implies the values of the WPA variables below are valid. If false, it indicates that this station did not send a WPA IE in its last association.

extremeWirelessClientAssocInfoWPAVersion.name: extremeWirelessClientAssocInfoWPAVersion
extremeWirelessClientAssocInfoWPAVersion.description: This value gives the version of WPA supported by this station. See IEEE 802.11i Draft 3.0 section 7 for meaning of various values.

extremeWirelessClientAssocInfoWPAIEMcast.name: extremeWirelessClientAssocInfoWPAIEMcastCipher
extremeWirelessClientAssocInfoWPAIEMcast.description: This value gives the single multicast cipher supported by this client.

extremeWirelessClientAssocInfoWPAUcastCi.name: extremeWirelessClientAssocInfoWPAUcastCipherCount
extremeWirelessClientAssocInfoWPAUcastCi.description: This gives the number of set bits in the ucast cipher variable below. In this case this number should always be 1.

extremeWirelessClientAssocInfoWPAUcastCi.name: extremeWirelessClientAssocInfoWPAUcastCipher
extremeWirelessClientAssocInfoWPAUcastCi.description: This gives the cipher suites which was requested by this client during its last assoc req.

extremeWirelessClientAssocInfoWPAKeyMgmt.name: extremeWirelessClientAssocInfoWPAKeyMgmtCount
extremeWirelessClientAssocInfoWPAKeyMgmt.description: This value gives the number of key management suites requested by this client in the last assoc. req message. It indicates the number of set bits in the mgmt suite variable below.

extremeWirelessClientAssocInfoWPAKeyMgmt.name: extremeWirelessClientAssocInfoWPAKeyMgmtSuite
extremeWirelessClientAssocInfoWPAKeyMgmt.description: Gives the key management suite requested by this client during its last association request.

extremeWirelessClientAssocIEBlob.name: extremeWirelessClientAssocIEBlob
extremeWirelessClientAssocIEBlob.description: This is the IE list sent in the association frame encoded as a series of TLVs.

extremeWirelessClientAuthInfoTable.name: extremeWirelessClientAuthInfoTable
extremeWirelessClientAuthInfoTable.description: This table contains one row per client on a wireless interface. It gives information about the authentication history and params of that client.

extremeWirelessClientAuthInfoEntry.name: extremeWirelessClientAuthInfoEntry
extremeWirelessClientAuthInfoEntry.description: Note that ifIndex here is virtual ifIndex (SSID).

extremeWirelessClientAuthInfoCurrentAuth.name: extremeWirelessClientAuthInfoCurrentAuth
extremeWirelessClientAuthInfoCurrentAuth.description: This gives the current MAC-layer authentication status of the client.

extremeWirelessClientAuthInfoTotalAuths.name: extremeWirelessClientAuthInfoTotalAuths
extremeWirelessClientAuthInfoTotalAuths.description: This is the total number of AUTH REQ packets received from this client since the last time the counters were cleared.

extremeWirelessClientAuthInfoTotalAuthRe.name: extremeWirelessClientAuthInfoTotalAuthResp
extremeWirelessClientAuthInfoTotalAuthRe.description: This is the total number of AUTH RESP packets sent to this client since the last time the counters were cleared.

extremeWirelessClientAuthInfoTotalAuthsO.name: extremeWirelessClientAuthInfoTotalAuthsOK
extremeWirelessClientAuthInfoTotalAuthsO.description: This is the total number of AUTH RESP packets sent to this client which carried a STATUS = OK message.

extremeWirelessClientAuthInfoTotalAuthsF.name: extremeWirelessClientAuthInfoTotalAuthsFailed
extremeWirelessClientAuthInfoTotalAuthsF.description: This is the total number of AUTH RESP packets sent to this client which carried a STATUS = Failed message.

extremeWirelessClientAuthInfoTotalDeauth.name: extremeWirelessClientAuthInfoTotalDeauthReq
extremeWirelessClientAuthInfoTotalDeauth.description: This is the total number of DEAUTH REQ packets sent from this client.

extremeWirelessClientAuthInfoTotalDeauth.name: extremeWirelessClientAuthInfoTotalDeauthResp
extremeWirelessClientAuthInfoTotalDeauth.description: This is the total number of DEAUTH RESP packets sent to this client.

extremeWirelessClientAuthInfoTotalOpen.name: extremeWirelessClientAuthInfoTotalOpen
extremeWirelessClientAuthInfoTotalOpen.description: This is the total number of AUTH REQ packets which requested open authentication from the AP.

extremeWirelessClientAuthInfoTotalShared.name: extremeWirelessClientAuthInfoTotalShared
extremeWirelessClientAuthInfoTotalShared.description: This is the total number of AUTH REQ packets which requested shared authentication from the AP.

extremeWirelessClientAuthInfoLastAuth.name: extremeWirelessClientAuthInfoLastAuth
extremeWirelessClientAuthInfoLastAuth.description: This is the sysUpTime the last time this client sent a request for authentication.

extremeWirelessClientAuthInfoLastAuthTyp.name: extremeWirelessClientAuthInfoLastAuthType
extremeWirelessClientAuthInfoLastAuthTyp.description: This is the last type of authentication requested by this client.

extremeWirelessClientAuthInfoLastError.name: extremeWirelessClientAuthInfoLastError
extremeWirelessClientAuthInfoLastError.description: This is the sysUpTime of the last authentication failure for this client.

extremeWirelessClientAuthInfoLastErrorTy.name: extremeWirelessClientAuthInfoLastErrorType
extremeWirelessClientAuthInfoLastErrorTy.description: This is the OID of the last error counter that was incremented for this client.

extremeWirelessClientAuthInfoErrorResour.name: extremeWirelessClientAuthInfoErrorResourceFailure
extremeWirelessClientAuthInfoErrorResour.description: This is the total number of authentication failures which have resulted from resource failures.

extremeWirelessClientAuthInfoErrorSequen.name: extremeWirelessClientAuthInfoErrorSequenceNum
extremeWirelessClientAuthInfoErrorSequen.description: This is the total number of authentication failures which have resulted from bad packet sequence numbers.

extremeWirelessClientAuthInfoErrorChalle.name: extremeWirelessClientAuthInfoErrorChallengeText
extremeWirelessClientAuthInfoErrorChalle.description: This is the total number of authentication failures which have resutled from challenge text mismatch.

extremeWirelessClientAuthInfoErrorTypeMi.name: extremeWirelessClientAuthInfoErrorTypeMismatch
extremeWirelessClientAuthInfoErrorTypeMi.description: This is the total number of authentication failures which have resutled from the requested authentication type (i.e. open/shared) not matching what this virutal interface is configured for.

extremeWirelessClientAuthInfoErrorKeyInd.name: extremeWirelessClientAuthInfoErrorKeyIndex
extremeWirelessClientAuthInfoErrorKeyInd.description: This is the total number of authentication failures which have resulted from key index mismatches.

extremeWirelessClientAuthInfoErrorOther.name: extremeWirelessClientAuthInfoErrorOther
extremeWirelessClientAuthInfoErrorOther.description: This is the total number of authentication failures which have resulted from unspecified errors.

extremeWirelessClientMACInfoTable.name: extremeWirelessClientMACInfoTable
extremeWirelessClientMACInfoTable.description: This table contains one entry per source MAC which has tried to authenticate with this virtual interface (SSID). Entries are created when AUTH or REATH REQ packets are received from new clients. Entries can be aged out, removed by management action, or overwritten by an overflow.

extremeWirelessClientMACInfoMinRSS.name: extremeWirelessClientMACInfoMinRSS
extremeWirelessClientMACInfoMinRSS.description: This gives the minimum RSS indication of any packet we have seen from this client. A value of 0 indicates that RSSI has been unavailable.

extremeWirelessClientMACInfoMaxRSS.name: extremeWirelessClientMACInfoMaxRSS
extremeWirelessClientMACInfoMaxRSS.description: This gives the maximum RSS indication of any packet we have seen from this client. A value of 0 indicates that RSSI has been unavailable.

extremeWirelessClientMACInfoAvgRSS.name: extremeWirelessClientMACInfoAvgRSS
extremeWirelessClientMACInfoAvgRSS.description: This gives the average RSS indication of any packet we have seen from this client. A value of 0 indicates that RSSI has been unavailable.

extremeWirelessClientMACInfoTotalProbeRe.name: extremeWirelessClientMACInfoTotalProbeReq
extremeWirelessClientMACInfoTotalProbeRe.description: This gives the total number of PROBE REQ packets recieved from this client since the counters have been cleared.

extremeWirelessClientMACInfoTotalAuthReq.name: extremeWirelessClientMACInfoTotalAuthReq
extremeWirelessClientMACInfoTotalAuthReq.description: This gives the total number of AUTH REQ packets recieved from this client since the counters have been cleared.

extremeWirelessClientMACInfoTotalAssocRe.name: extremeWirelessClientMACInfoTotalAssocReq
extremeWirelessClientMACInfoTotalAssocRe.description: This gives the total number of ASSOC REQ packets recieved from this client since the counters have been cleared.

extremeWirelessClientMACInfoTotalReAssoc.name: extremeWirelessClientMACInfoTotalReAssocReq
extremeWirelessClientMACInfoTotalReAssoc.description: This gives the total number of REASSOC REQ packets recieved from this client since the counters have been cleared.

extremeWirelessClientMACInfoTotalDeAssoc.name: extremeWirelessClientMACInfoTotalDeAssocReq
extremeWirelessClientMACInfoTotalDeAssoc.description: This gives the total number of DEASSOC REQ packets recieved from this client since the counters have been cleared.

extremeWirelessClientMACInfoTotalDeAuthR.name: extremeWirelessClientMACInfoTotalDeAuthReq
extremeWirelessClientMACInfoTotalDeAuthR.description: This gives the total number of DEAUTH REQ packets recieved from this client since the counters have been cleared.

extremeWirelessClientMACInfoTotalPsPoll.name: extremeWirelessClientMACInfoTotalPsPoll
extremeWirelessClientMACInfoTotalPsPoll.description: This gives the total number of PS POLL packets recieved from this client since the counters have been cleared.

extremeWirelessClientMACInfoTotalData.name: extremeWirelessClientMACInfoTotalData
extremeWirelessClientMACInfoTotalData.description: This gives the total number of data frames received from this client since the counters have been cleared.

extremeWirelessClientMACInfoNavValue.name: extremeWirelessClientMACInfoNavValue
extremeWirelessClientMACInfoNavValue.description: TODO: Is this an average, total, what?

extremeWirelessClientSizeCounterTable.name: extremeWirelessClientSizeCounterTable
extremeWirelessClientSizeCounterTable.description: There is one entry in this table for each client which has tried to authenticate with this virtual interface. A new entry is created when an AUTH or REATH REQ packet is received from a new station. Entries are removed by management action, timeout or overwritten due to overflow. Entries in this table are also indexed by virtual interface. A client which has tried to authenticate to multiple virtual interfaces may have more than one entry in this table.

extremeWirelessClientFrameSizeReXmit64.description: This gives the number of frags retransmitted to this client which were less than or equal to 64 bytes in length.
